title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Beat eggs gently with sugar. Add oil, water and pumpkin. Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Fold in nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in 3 large loaf pans or 5 small pans.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, apples and oil.
Let stand while preparing remainder.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients mixed together.
Bake at 350° a little over an hour.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to use, at least 30 minutes.

title: mock potato salad
directions: Prepare cauliflower according to package directions and let cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients with cauliflower.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter and sprinkle bottom with pecans and coconut. Mix cake mix according to directions on box and pour over the pecans and coconut. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 stick butter. Spoon over cake batter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender; pour into a 10-inch pie pan that's been floured and well greased.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Mix together, adding raisins and chopped nutmeats last.
Drop by teaspoon and bake in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: irish italian spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in hot oil; add meat and seasoning.
Then brown lightly.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add both soups, cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Arrange spaghetti on hot platter and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour pineapple in bottom. Spoon cherry pie filling over.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over top. Put chunks of butter evenly on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 325° for about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars.
Put 1 garlic clove, 1 spice clove, pepper and dill seed to each jar.
Mix coarse salt to vinegar and water; mix well.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a rolling boil and pour into jars.
Seal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring and combine with cinnamon, salt, soda and nuts and set aside.
With mixer on low speed, mix well the eggs, oil and sugar; add carrots.
Mix dry ingredients with batter.
(Do not beat very much.) Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: raspberry oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter.
Combine dry cake mix and oats in a large bowl.
Stir in melted butter until crumbly. Measure in half (about 3 cups) in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Press firmly to cover bottom.

title: florentine quiche
directions: Saute onion until soft in 1/2 stick butter or oleo.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Add milk, shredded cheese, spinach and cooled sauteed onion.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° until crust is brown and quiche is set well in the center.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before serving.
Good with picante.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
In a bowl, dissolve the yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Mix in flour with hand until dough is easy to handle.
Place greased-side-up in greased bowl.
Cover with waxed paper and a damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs and butter, then add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour in pie crust and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter flavored Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; beat into creamed mixture until blended.
Stir in walnuts, chocolate chunks, white chocolate pieces and milk chocolate chips.
Drop 2 level tablespoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix
well
and
refrigerate.
If
using
a blender, put liquids in first, then sugar, salt and pepper.
Cut onion into pieces and add garlic whole; blend.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs and butter; spread in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix the powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese; pour over first layer.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in cereal, chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop by level tablespoons onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: mushroom turnovers
directions: Knead the cream cheese, butter, flour and salt into a dough. Divide the dough into several portions and roll the dough between 2 pieces of waxed paper to a thickness of 1/8-inch.
When all dough is rolled out, put the sheets in the refrigerator to firm up.
(Be sure they are flat.)

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together and spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: mexican lime marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients with 6 skinless chicken breasts; marinate for 4 to 6 hours, then barbecue.

title: snowballs(no bake cookies)
directions: Combine butter, sugar, dates and egg. Cook 10 minutes in double boiler, stirring constantly. Let cool. Add all other ingredients and form into balls. Roll in shredded coconut.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix mayo, cheese, eggs and soup.
Stir in asparagus.
Pour into casserole dish.
Place casserole in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place apples in greased square pan. Combine remaining ingredients (mix with fork).
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: deluxe egg salad sandwich
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and butter.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in celery, mayo, onion, sugar, horseradish, lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Fold in eggs.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Let stand at room temperature about 15 minutes before making sandwiches.
Add more mayo, if desired.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon onto ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: oriental beef stir-fry
directions: Cut steak into thin slices.
Cut green onions into 1-inch pieces.
Combine broth, cornstarch and soy sauce in a small bowl; mix until cornstarch dissolves and set aside.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each. Add flour, sour cream and soda. Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: walnut topping
directions: In blender combine walnuts, flour, sugars, cinnamon and salt. Chop fine.
Add butter.
Blend only enough to distribute evenly to form a crumbly mixture.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve jello
in
hot
water,
then add marshmallows. Stir until
melted,
then add mayonnaise, cabbage, carrots and pineapple.
Mix well
and
refrigerate until it starts to set; then whip the milk until it forms stiff peaks.
Add to mixture by folding in; add nuts.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, butter and egg yolks.
Add milk.
Cook until thick.
Beat egg whites with 4 tablespoons sugar.
Pour over pies.
Bake until brown.

title: onion dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and gets bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: white fudge icing
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until thick.
Add 4 tablespoons to stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue to cook until a good thread test, add to mixture and beat well.

title: chocolate strawberry pie
directions: Crust:
Combine 1 cup Oreo crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom and sides of lightly greased 9-inch deep dish pie pan. Bake in 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pecan country chicken
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter.
Cool.
Mix with cream cheese, mustard and thyme.
Spread on each piece of chicken. Fold over ends and roll up, pressing edges to seal.
Mix pecans, bread crumbs and parsley in bowl.
Dip chicken in butter, then in crumbs, turning to coat.
Place on greased cookie sheet, seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Good with rice.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Clean and cut broccoli into small pieces.
Steam until tender. Do not drain!
Melt butter, then stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Stir in chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Simmer until it thickens.
Add broccoli and liquid, salt, pepper and half and half.
Heat, but do not boil.
Add cheese, if desired.
This is a large recipe.
Half is enough for a family meal.

title: oatmeal batter bread
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in water.
Add egg and dry ingredients.
Spread in greased pan and brush with butter. Sprinkle on a little dry oatmeal.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until brown and crisp.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Break up 1/2 of cake in small pieces and place on bottom of deep bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sliced strawberries and flavor with the desired amount of sugar.
Put 1/2 of strawberries on top of cake with some of the juice.

title: green tomatoes relish
directions: Bring to a boiling point and cook 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove spice bag and pour into jars.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.

title: butter crisp cookies
directions: Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: spicy southern gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, molasses and oleo together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture with 1 cup boiling water.
Beat well.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for
35 minutes.
Serves 20.

title: stuffed cabbage(golabki)
directions: Mix together pork, beef, veal, eggs, onions, rice and salt and pepper.
Place cabbage (from which the core has been removed) into hot water to soften leaves.
Take approximately 3 tablespoons of meat mixture and place it in a cabbage leaf and wrap it.
Take can of tomato soup, some water and crushed tomatoes and salt and pepper and pour over cabbage rolls (after the cabbage rolls have been in the oven for 25 minutes).
Put in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes about 120.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cook cherries, pineapple, sugar and flour 5 minutes.
Remove and add jello and food coloring.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour in crust and chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Make brownies according to package instructions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix mousse according to directions; do not chill.
Crumble brownies.
Place 1/2 brownies, 1/2 mousse, 1/2 crushed candy bars and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Chill 8 hours.

title: ruglach
directions: In mixing bowl, place flour, butter and cream cheese and mix well until dough forms.
Divide into 4 balls of pastry, wrap in plastic wrap or waxed paper and refrigerate at least 2 hours or longer.

title: florida pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 deep dish graham cracker pie crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: shortbread pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together butter, flour and sugar and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Beat together all other ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 325° and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Mix together salt and vinegar.
Pour into quart jar.
Place dill and garlic clove in bottom of jar, then layer cucumbers and dill.
Place dill and 1 tablespoon whole pickling spice on top. Fill jars with cold water and seal.

title: meat balls
directions: Make into balls in size of lemon.
Put 1 can tomato soup in saucepan.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine, dash of cloves and celery salt to taste.
Add meatballs and simmer for 1 hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Cut flour, Crisco and salt in mixing bowl until it resembles cornmeal.
Add milk and egg.
Roll out on floured board and cut in strips.
Let dry for 30 minutes before placing over your boiled and deboned chicken.
Cook for 20 minutes without taking the lid off the pan.

title: rancho beans
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in salad oil; add ground beef and brown.
Drain and pour into a casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: coriander-orange chicken
directions: Blend coriander, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Rub into chicken. Melt butter; brown chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken. Reduce heat and cook onions and garlic, covered, until softened. Add orange rind, juice and broth.
Bring to a boil and boil until syrupy.
Return chicken to pan and coat well in sauce.
Cook until heated through.
Halve orange, lengthwise, and slice crosswise and fan around chicken.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender in boiling salted water. Set carrots, onion and bell pepper aside.
Heat the rest of the ingredients just enough to blend well and pour over carrots. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix together milk, eggs, salt and enough flour to make a stiff batter.
(This also makes a good noodle dough.)

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Place in bowl with 1 cup of sugar, Milnot, milk, vanilla, egg yolks and melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a 10 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In medium saucepan combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper.
Add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through and stir often. Serves 4.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler.
When smooth and creamy, remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: overnight cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; let stand for 2 hours. Whip the cream and add marshmallows and pineapple. Add cranberry mixture. Pour into mold. Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.

title: hamburger-cabbage bake
directions: Cook and stir beef in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain. Stir in cabbage, onion, 2 tablespoons water, the salt, caraway seed and pepper.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is tender, about 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on flour covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 4-inch rounds; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make hole in center of each round to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Spoon beef into shells; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake light brown 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with catsup or chili sauce.

title: dad's chili
directions: Brown hamburger, drain well.
Rinse beans.
Mix soup, meat, beans, seasonings (water if desired) and chopped onion.
Cook over medium heat 2 to 4 hours.
The longer the better tasting.

title: pralines
directions: Combine in heavy pot the cream, water, sugar and oleo.
Cook over medium heat, stirring fairly constantly.
When caramelized brown spots begin to appear, continue stirring.
Drop small amount in cup of water.
When this makes a ringing sound against side of metal cup, the pralines are ready.
Quickly add vanilla and pecans and quickly drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
(If it hardens too quickly, return pot to stove, add a little water and heat again until ready.)
Allow pralines to cool before removing from the wax paper.

title: chunky chicken casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 of the cubed bread in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Combine chicken, onions, mayonnaise and salt; spread over bread cubes.
Arrange remaining bread over chicken.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Pour over bread cubes.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Spoon soup over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese the last 5 minutes of baking time.
Serves 6.

title: buttery onion soup
directions: In a large kettle, saute onion in butter over low heat until tender and transparent, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Blend in flour.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dressing and vanilla, then gradually add cold water.
Mix until smooth.
Place in greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: texas turtles
directions: Line
large
cookie
sheets with waxed paper; set aside. In medium
sized
heavy
saucepan,
over
low heat, melt peanut butter chips with 1/2 can of condensed milk.
Remove from heat; stir in
vinegar.
Drop
by
generous
half teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart on
prepared cookie sheets.
Place 3 pecan halves on top, pressing in
slightly
with points touching; set aside.
In top of double
boiler,
over
simmering water, melt chocolate bits with remaining condensed
milk.
Remove from heat but keep over warm water,
stir
in
vanilla.
Spoon heaping teaspoonfuls of chocolate
over pecan clusters, spreading lightly.
Chill until firm, about
hours.
Store
between layers of waxed paper in airtight tins.
Makes 48.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef and green onions until fine.
Mix with softened cream cheese and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Eat with Ritz crackers.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in a mixing bowl and let stand 10 minutes.
Blend oil, vanilla and egg with the apples.
Then combine the dry ingredients and mix in well.
Stir in raisins.

title: cinnamon coffeecake
directions: Cream together butter and 1 cup sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well. Add vanilla and lemon juice. Sift together flour, baking powder and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Blend brown sugar, 1 tablespoon sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour half the batter into a buttered tube pan. Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over batter, then add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes. Remove and serve warm.

title: enchiladas
directions: Fry 1/3 cup each in ungreased pan.

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix together and cook like hush puppies.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Remove from heat when it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Slowly pour syrup over salted, stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue beating until candy holds its shape when dropped from spoon.
Mix in vanilla.
Turn onto greased pan and cut into squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in bananas.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to banana mixture.
Mix until just blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue bean salad
directions: Drain the first 4 ingredients well. Add the celery, green peppers and onions.

title: tuna buns
directions: Mix ingredients, except buns.
Split and stuff buns with mixture.
Wrap in foil and place in 250° oven to warm for 30 minutes.

title: spicy bean pot
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and cook 35 minutes.
If using crock-pot, cover and cook on high 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: pepper relish
directions: Place all ingredients together in enamel or stainless steel pot.
Bring to boil, then simmer 15 minutes, uncovered.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal and process 10 minutes.
Makes about 9 pints.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, cornstarch and food coloring together until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and stir in 3 Tbsp. strawberry flavored gelatin (dry).
Cool.
In the meantime, mix and bake No Roll Pie Crust.
Put fresh strawberries in pie crust and pour in cooled pie mixture.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate-cherry filled cookies
directions: Stir flour, cocoa, salt, soda and baking powder.
Set aside.

title: trash
directions: Lightly butter a jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix cereal, peanuts, raisins and banana chips in a large bowl.
Mix pudding and honey in a small saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Boil and stir one minute; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal mixture; toss until evenly coated.
Spread in pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Break into bite size pieces.
Store in covered container.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add beer and stir well.
Pour batter into a greased loaf pan.
Cover and let rise 1 hour or until double.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until lightly brown.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: new york slaw
directions: Thoroughly mix together all the ingredients; cover and chill. Keeps well.

title: fiesta pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl, stir in milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except salsa and sour cream; mix well.
Pour mixture into greased 9-inch microwavable pie plate.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir edges of mixture into center and from center to outside edges, smoothing out surface.
Cover.
Microwave 4 minutes or until center is no longer wet.
Remove from microwave and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve immediately with salsa and sour cream.

title: double apricot bread
directions: In a blender, process canned apricots until smooth.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and pumpkin pie spice.
In another mixing bowl, combine the eggs, milk, cooking oil and the apricot puree.
Add the egg mixture to the flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Stir in the dried apricots.
Pour the batter into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in the pans on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Slice and serve with butter.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows.
Add other ingredients.
Mold in any shape desired.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground chuck and then strain grease off meat.
Add all other ingredients and let simmer on stove or in crock-pot.
The longer it simmers, the better it is.

title: oven-fried chicken-rice casserole
directions: Put dry soup mix, rice, soups and water into a large greased flat pan and mix.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of mixture.
Bake 1
hour at 350°.

title: vegetable cornmeal dumplings
directions: Scald milk; add 1/4 cup margarine, sugar and 1 teaspoon salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add dissolved yeast, 1 cup flour, cornmeal and egg to milk mixture, stirring to combine.
Add enough additional flour (1 1/2 to 2 cups) to make a soft dough and knead lightly until dough is smooth.
Place dough in a greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Cook celery, carrots, onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt, covered, in 2 tablespoons margarine or drippings for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: urasion chicken
directions: Layer chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour half over chicken.
Bake in oven at 350°, basting every 15 minutes with remaining ingredients.
Turn chicken after 45 minutes and keep basting until done.

title: quick butter-fluff rolls
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt, shortening and soda.
Cool to lukewarm.
Let yeast stand in water for 5 minutes; add to milk mixture.
Add flour to make a soft dough; knead until smooth.
Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in strips about 1 1/2-inches wide.
Spread strips with butter and make layers of three; cut in 1 1/2-inch pieces and place, cut side down, in well-greased muffin pans.
Brush tops with melted shortening.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen small rolls.

title: puffcorn snack
directions: In large pan, mix brown sugar, corn syrup and butter. Bring to a boil and simmer for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda. Pour over the snack food and mix well. Spread on lightly buttered sheet cake pan. Spread well; place in 275° oven for 30 minutes. Stir once while baking. Spoon out on waxed paper to cool. When cool, break apart. Store in airtight container. Nuts or coconut may be added before being stored.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in shell.
Mix all other ingredients except margarine.
Pour over rhubarb and dot with margarine.
Place top crust on top and sprinkle well with sugar and nutmeg or cinnamon. Bake 50 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Do not use margarine as substitute.

title: irish cottage cheese pie
directions: Line a pie plate with pie crust (bought or made). Start creaming the cheese in mixer bowl at low speed, gradually adding milk, flour, butter, vanilla, eggs, sugar and salt.
Pour into pie dish. Bake at 400° to start for 15 minutes, then 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour.
If desired, blow cinnamon on top before putting in the oven.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese) in a large bowl.
Pour half of mixture into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish and top with half of the cheese.
Pour remaining mixture into dish and top with the other half of the cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: diced chicken breasts with cashew nuts
directions: In a bowl, combine the chicken breasts, egg white, bamboo shoots, sugar, cornstarch, cooking oil, soy sauce, rice wine, salt and ajinomoto.
Blend thoroughly.
Fry the cashew nuts in cooking oil until crisp and golden brown.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms in cooking oil.
Add 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Pour in the chicken mixture.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with sesame oil.
Serve hot with fried cashew nuts on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: holiday macaroons
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Slowly add sugar; beat until thick. Fold in flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Blend in lemon rind and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: 3 week slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle sugar over top of chopped mixture.
Bring to a boil, vinegar, oil, salt and celery seed; pour over vegetable mixture and stir well. Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for 3 weeks.

title: overnight caramel rolls
directions: Place rolls in a greased tube pan.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over rolls.
Combine pudding mix and brown sugar and sprinkle half over rolls.
Pour remaining butter over and sprinkle with rest of brown sugar mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts over.
Let rise 8 hours or overnight at room temperature.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zippy deviled eggs
directions: Shell and slice eggs in half, length wise.
Remove yolks and set whites aside.
In a bowl mash yolks; stir in mayonnaise, chile sauce, mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Pack or stuff into egg white.
Sprinkle with paprika,
refrigerate until serving.

title: ma-ma's ham loaf(jason's favorite meat loaf)
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: beef house rolls
directions: Mix the 3/4 cup water, sugar, salt and margarine.
Bring to boil and then cool until lukewarm.
Mix yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water until dissolved.
Add to sugar the margarine mixture.
Add egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour (use more if sticky) and mix.
Place in greased bowl and let rise.

title: chow-chow
directions: Tie spices in bag;
boil with vinegar 15 minutes.
Then add all the chopped
ingredients.
Simmer
until
hot and well flavored.
Pack into jars and seal.

title: pita bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, soften yeast in warm water. Add 2 c of flour, the shortening and salt. Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl. Beat 3 minutes at high speed. Stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can mix with a spoon. Turn out onto lightly floured surface. Knead in enough of the remaining flour to form a moderately soft dough that is smooth and elastic (3 to 5 minutes total). Cover; let rest in warm place for 15 minutes. Divide into 12 equal portions. Roll each between floured hands into very smooth balls.Cover with plastic wrap or damp cloth; let rest 10 minutes. Using fingers, gently flatten balls, without creasing dough. Cover let rest 10 minutes. (Keep dough pieces covered until ready to use. On well floured surface, lightly roll one piece of dough at a time into 7 inch round, turning dough over once. Do not stretch, puncture or crease dough. Work with enough flour that so dough does not stick. Place on baking sheet.

title: vanilla butternut pound cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add eggs, beating well. Add flour alternating with milk.
Fold in the flavoring until well blended.
Start to bake in a cold oven.
Set temperature at 325°. Bake for 1 3/4 hours.
(Fills a large tube cake pan.)

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1/2-inch wide strips.
In small bowl, combine mustard, wine, soy sauce, garlic and black pepper.
In nonmetal dish, pour mustard mixture over chicken.
Cover; chill 1 to 2 hours, stirring chicken once.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken mixture in margarine until no longer pink.
Add vegetables; cook and stir until tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.

title: banana-pineapple jello salad
directions: Add nuts, pineapple, marshmallows and bananas to shimmery jello.
Let set.

title: czechoslovakian squares
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat until light.
Add egg yolks, blend.
Gradually beat in flour.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon half of mixture into pan.
Spread with jam to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Cover with remaining dough.
(You may have to pat out to cover lower layer.)
Bake 1 hour at 325° in a preheated oven or until lightly browned.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray a 10-inch pie plate with Pam. Cook meat and onion.
Stir in seasoning mix. Cook to blend. Spread in pie plate and top with chilies. Beat together the skim milk, Bisquick and egg until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture. Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Continue baking until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cook 8 to 10 minutes. Top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: yes! another chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan. Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pasta with dill and tomatoes
directions: Prepare the pasta according to the package directions; drain. Transfer the pasta to a serving bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and toss well.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 4.

title: creamy yogurt potato salad
directions: In large bowl, mix well mayonnaise, yogurt, cider vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, onions and celery.
Toss to coat well; cover and chill at least 4 hours or overnight. Sprinkle with chopped parsley, boiled egg wedges and tomatoes. Keep refrigerated.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon. Add buttermilk, butter and eggs. Beat at low speed of an electric mixer until dry ingredients are moistened; beat at medium speed an additional 3 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake icing
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan and cook slowly until it thickens.
Remove from stove and let cool.
Spread between layers and around.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Thinly slice the mushrooms and onions.
Saute in butter for 5 minutes.
Slowly add the flour and the hot broth, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the sour cream and stir.
Good with grilled steak and baked potatoes.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Press hamburger flat in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square cake pan. Sprinkle with onion salt.
Pour soup over meat.
Sprinkle uncooked peas over soup.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cranberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and baking soda.
In another bowl mix egg, plain yogurt and oil.
Combine the 2 bowls.
Add chopped apples and chopped dried cranberries.
Put mixture in pan; mix butter, oatmeal, chopped almonds and cinnamon.
Place on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: reduced calorie stuffed fish fillets
directions: Combine celery, onions and 1/2 cup broth in pan.
Cover and steam over medium heat (about 7 minutes) until vegetables are tender.
Stir in bread crumbs, parsley, nuts, lemon juice, peel and salt if desired.
Place half of fish fillets in greased shallow baking dish.
Top with vegetable mixture, then remaining fish fillets.
Pour remaining broth over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
For special presentation spread 1/4 of filling on each of 4 thin fillets.
Roll up, secure with toothpick, cover and bake as directed.
Cover loosely.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings, 216 calories; 12 grams fat each.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into patties.
Cook in skillet in hot oil until brown on each side, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter; add 2 cups sugar gradually, beating until very light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, very well.
Mix in cream and vanilla.
Fold in flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1/3 batter in well greased and floured Bundt pan or a 9-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 of nut mixture.
Spoon remaining batter in and sprinkle with remaining nut mixture.
Bake about 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes and cool on rack.

title: p.j. johnston's spinach stuffed onion rings
directions: Mix beer, flour
and
salt.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Slice onions 1-inch thick.
Separate
into rings (6 to 8 outer rings to an onion;
discard centers).
Heat oil in deep-fat fryer to 375°. Dip rings
in
batter.
Fry until golden brown, about 2 to	3 minutes.
Drain
on
paper
towels
(store
at
room temperature, covered, until
final baking).
Place rings on an oiled baking sheet and fill with spinach.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until spinach bubbles.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients in small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, tear lettuce into small pieces and mix thoroughly with chilled mix.
Serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese together.
Stir in other ingredients.
Makes about 3 cups of dip.
Good with raw vegetables and crackers.

title: unrolled cabbage rolls
directions: Spray pan, add onion and garlic, saute.
Add broth and rice. Bring to a boil and simmer for 25 minutes.
Pre-cook cabbage and chop.
Combine browned meat rice, egg white, parsley, margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spray 3 quart casserole, line with half of the cabbage.
Layer meat mixture, then rest of the cabbage.
Mix soup and water and pour over cabbage.
Cover and bake at 350 for one hour, then for 45 minutes at 325.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop ham and onion finely.
Place in a large bowl.
Add cheese, egg, pepper and mustard.
Stir to combine.
Spray mini-muffin pan with vegetable oil.
Unroll crescent rolls and press dough into one large rectangle.
Cut rectangle into 24 pieces using a pizza cutter.
Place dough pieces in mini-muffin pan cups.
Place filling in cup.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: checkerboard cake
directions: Cut cake into 1-inch pieces.
Beat egg yolks and sugar.
Melt the bitter chocolate and add to egg mixture.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/3 cup cold water.
Fill cup with boiling water.
Beat the egg whites stiff and add to mixture.
Blend in cake pieces.
Pack into a spring-form or angel food tin.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken salad or cucumber rounds
directions: Chop the chicken and add the mayonnaise and dill.
Cut the cucumbers into round slices and put a small amount of chicken salad on top of each one.
Put a small piece of parsley on the top of each chicken salad mound.

title: barbecue marinated steak cubes
directions: Marinate cubed beef all day or overnight in metal bowl, covered with plastic wrap.
(Plastic bowl will absorb the marinade.)
Put on skewers and grill 10 minutes, 5 minutes on each side.

title: crab thingers
directions: Combine all ingredients except English muffins.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze 10 minutes or until needed.
Cut into 1/4ths or 1/6ths.
Broil on a rack in a cookie sheet until browned and bubbling.
Should be put about 8 inches from the broiler so it can cook throughout before browning.

title: crepes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth. For each crepe, butter an 8-inch skillet; heat over medium heat until butter is bubbly.
Pour scant 1/4 cup batter into skillet. Immediately rotate pan until batter covers bottom of pan.
Cook until light brown; turn and brown on other side.
Makes 10 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain and set aside.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Firmly chop stems.
Reserve mushroom caps.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter or oleo, cook stems, onion, garlic, parsley, salt and oregano until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Mix in bread crumbs and cheese.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Place, stuffed side up, on a rack in broiler pan. Broil 8 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.

title: chicken casserole(marie hardman's)
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut in chunks.
Brown (in butter) carrots, green pepper and onions.
Add to browned mixture, soup, 3/4 package stuffing, sour cream, chicken and broth.
Mix well. Pour mix into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake for 35 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: brown eyed susans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Dough will be thinner than most drop cookie dough.
Best when chilled.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: shrimp wrapped in bacon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap shrimp with bacon; fasten with toothpicks.
Place in baking pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven; drain and serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, put a layer of corn chips, then a layer of tuna, then a layer of mixed vegetables.
Top with a can of cream of chicken soup.
Repeat directions and top off with can of cream of celery soup.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbling and a little brown on top.
Makes a complete meal.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Put in water with minced onions, celery flakes, salt and pepper to taste and garlic salt.
Simmer whole chicken gently for 1 1/2 hours.
Lift chicken out.
Strain liquid.
Put liquid back in Dutch oven.
Add chicken bouillon cubes.
Simmer until dissolved.
Carefully skin and debone chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Add to liquid and bring to boil.
Taste for enough salt.
Slice flour tortillas; drop into rolling boil.
Put lid on; reduce heat for 5 minutes.
Do not lift lid!!
Cut off flame and let set for 20 minutes.
Add enough milk to make liquid look like a sauce and add 1 tablespoon butter.
Put flame on to add butter and milk.
Keep on flame until butter is melted, but do not boil.
Ready to serve.

title: sara's taco soup
directions: Add all the ingredients to broth.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
This is good served with the restaurant style Tostitos.

title: karmel korn
directions: Mix butter,
brown
sugar, corn syrup and salt in large pot. Boil,
stew
constantly
for
minutes.
Do
not stir. Remove from
heat	and
add vanilla and soda.
Stir. Gradually pour over popped
corn.
This should be in large baking dish. Bake in
oven at 250°.
Stir every 10 minutes until 30 minutes of time.
Remove; cool.
Break up and put in tight container.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, syrup and vinegar together.
Boil until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put mixture in glass dish or appropriate container.
Cool and enjoy!

title: zucchini cookies(3 dozen)
directions: Sift together flour, salt, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix all together and then add raisins and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by spoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large frypan and saute chopped onion.
Add broccoli that has been washed and cut into bite size pieces.
Let cook for approximately 5 minutes.
Add rice and cream of chicken soup.
Add grated cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake until bubbly around the edge and bread crumbs are turning brown.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt, sugar, chili powder, garlic and basil.
Drain grease.
Add tomato paste, sauce and water.
Cook together until it boils.
Ladle into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add cheese and noodles.
Keep repeating, ending with cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Can be frozen for another meal.
Important: Noodles are not cooked!

title: yogurt delight
directions: Sprinkle plain yogurt on graham crackers.
Sprinkle small amount of brown sugar over yogurt.
Add raisins or other fruit. Top with other graham crackers.
Eat as a nutritious snack or dessert.

title: onion salad
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour this into a bowl and put in refrigerator until it just starts to jell.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and mix together. Return to refrigerator until set.

title: glace for fresh fruit pies
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add to 1 cup water.
Cook until shiny clear.
Add 3 tablespoons Jell-O.
Remove from heat and stir well.
Cool, then add to the sliced fruit and pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: carrot layer cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together until well blended.
Add honey in a fine stream, beating constantly.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to batter in 2 additions, beating well after each addition. Fold in carrots and add pecans.
Pour into 2 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, until cake tests done with toothpick.
Cool on wire racks, then frost.

title: martin's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and cottage cheese. Add and blend eggs, vanilla and lemon juice.
Gradually fold in flour, cornstarch and sugar.
Add and blend sour cream with butter or margarine.
Blend well and pour into a 9-inch loose bottom cheesecake type pan that has been greased and lined with graham cracker meal crust.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Open the oven door one notch and let stand for 2 hours with oven turned off.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: mama's ribbon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add and mix well. Divide dough into 3 parts.
Add finely cut cherries to one part, chocolate and nuts to another and poppy seed to the last part. Chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Reserve 10 cookies; crush the rest.
Mix crumbs with melted oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk and cream cheese.
Spread over crumbs.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Crush reserved 10 cookies and sprinkle on top of cake.
Refrigerate.
Flavor is better if prepared 1 day ahead of serving.
Spoon out of pan (cannot be cut).

title: baked carrots and apples
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Combine carrots and apple slices. Turn into 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with sugar and spice mix. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with dash of paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place all ingredients into pan. Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: polish pierogi dumplings with fillings
directions: Mix flour, egg and salt.
Add enough water to make medium soft dough.
Knead until blisters appear.
Divide dough into 2 portions.
Roll each portion thin; cut into 2-inch squares.
Place a spoonful of filling in each.
Fold in half to make a triangle. Pinch edges.
Drop into boiling water until pierogi comes to top, about 10 minutes.
After pierogi are boiled and drained, brown butter in skillet and pour over pierogi.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread potatoes in dish.
Pour melted oleo on top.
In a bowl, mix soup, sour cream, Cheez Whiz and onions.
Spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: instant sauce or drizzle
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add desired liquid and mix well. Drizzle over puddings, cakes, etc.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add sugar.

title: chicken spinach casserole
directions: Mix the chicken, cream of chicken soup, garlic powder and rosemary.
Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix with noodles and cottage cheese.
Layer: chicken mix, spinach mix and Mozzarella cheese in 2-quart baking dish, ending with chicken.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli cheese fettucini
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oleo, cook garlic 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in chicken, soup, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over hot cooked fettucini. Toss to coat. Garnish with parsley.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and green pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together. Cover and cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: carrots and apples(great with ham or pork)
directions: Peel
and
cut
carrots
in 3/4-inch strips.
Cook until almost done.
Drain.
Add to apple pie mix, sugar and cinnamon. Dot
with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or put in microwave on High for 1/2 hour.
Serve with ham or pork.

title: chocolate drizzle cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl combine flour, oats, sugar and butter.
Beat at low until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remaining mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until mixture is lightly browned.

title: hello dolly brownies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press graham cracker crumbs into butter.
Add layer chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour milk on top; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 15 servings.

title: foolproof key lime pie
directions: Beat together in order given until light and fluffy.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: low-fat oven brown chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip in skim milk.
Roll in a mixture of cereals and Mrs. Dash seasonings.
Arrange in a baking pan.

title: old fashioned candied yams
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in quarters or slices.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg, add butter, add vanilla, salt and water.
Cover and simmer over medium heat until liquid forms a syrup. Remove from heat and serve.

title: german slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, slice onions thin.
Combine cabbage and onions. Place sugar on top.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Bring to boil the remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour with corn flakes crushed on top.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix butter and graham cracker crumbs together and press in bottom of pan.
Then mix next 4 ingredients and pour over graham cracker crumbs and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled figs
directions: Leave stems on figs; wash and drain.
Put spices, sugar and vinegar in large agate pot and
boil for 20 minutes.
Drop figs into boiling syrup and cut	off
heat.
Cover
with
thin dish towel and let stand overnight.

title: beef casserole
directions: Saute together beef, lard, salt, onion, celery and green pepper.
Add soup, soy sauce and water.
Add cooked noodles and mix well.
Add sour cream and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle the top with almonds.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add flavoring.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Then flatten with a buttered glass dipped in sugar. Bake eight to ten minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cooler
directions: Mix pineapple chunks and juice with bananas.
Add oranges, fruit cocktail and coconut, stirring slowly.
Add the instant lemon mix into fruit and juice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Pudding will set in fruit juice.
Refrigerate.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, rice and garlic.
Salt and pepper to your taste. Chop onion with meat or slice on top of cabbage rolls.
Wrap cabbage leaf around 2 tablespoons of meat mix.
Arrange in a baking dish.
Mix lemon juice to taste with tomato juice.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover; bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cooking chocolate
directions: Combine and melt on stove.
This makes 1 square or 1 ounce unsweetened baking chocolate.

title: low calorie viennese hot cocoa mix
directions: In a large bowl, whisk or stir all ingredients until very well blended.
Pack in clean, dry jars with tight fitting lids.

title: orange sheet cake
directions: Mix candy orange slices, pineapple, coconut and pecans in one cup of flour.
Set aside.

title: oriental beef skillet
directions: Brown narrow slices of meat quickly, 1/2 amount at a time. Remove meat from pan.
Cook celery and onion 2 to 3 minutes until tender-crispy.
Add water and soy sauce to mushroom soup and bring to boiling, then return meat to pan.
Add spinach to skillet. Cover and bring to boil.
Add bean sprouts for 1 minute, then serve.

title: mor
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown meat and chopped onion in skillet.
Combine vegetables and soup and add other ingredients.
Cook on low heat for about 45 minutes.
Put in casserole and bake until brown on top.
Cheese may be sprinkled on top.
Can be frozen indefinitely.

title: congealed salad
directions: Melt jello in water; let cool.
Add pineapple (juice and all). Add cottage cheese; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into any serving dish and top with Mandarin orange slices.
Cool a few hours before serving.

title: santa's fudge
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy 2-quart pan.
In it combine sugar, cocoa, salt, water and butter.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook to soft ball stage (234°), stirring only if necessary.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm (110°), without stirring.
Add vanilla.
Beat vigorously until fudge becomes very thick and starts to gloss.
Quickly stir in nuts and spread in buttered pan.
Cut when firm.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to soft ball stage (238° to 240°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir until mixture thickens, becomes creamy and cloudy and pecans stay suspended in mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together shortening and sugar. Beat in the eggs until smooth.
Add water, zucchini and vanilla. Mix together well.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzel, margarine and sugar.
Press in 13x10 pan and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix Jello, boiling water and strawberries until dissolved.
Refrigerate 30 minutes. Mix cream cheese and sugar, fold in Cool Whip and spread over pretzel mixture, pour cooled Jello on top and refrigerate.
Let set 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: chow you gai
directions: Stew chicken.
Debone while hot and tear into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle
1 tablespoon of salt and 3 teaspoons of soy sauce and sesame seed over chicken.
Scatter green onions over chicken next.
Heat
oil
until it almost smokes.
Pour on top of chicken
and
serve immediately.
Serve with rice and fruit salad. Serves 5 to 6.

title: pecan honeymoon squares
directions: Preheat oven
to
Blend Crisco and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Add
cup flour and salt.
Stir in milk.
Pat evenly in greased 9
x
9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until light brown. Beat
eggs;
add
1 cup brown sugar and vanilla. Beat
until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour onto mixture in
pan. Bake
at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Frost and
garnish
with cherries, if desired. Cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Put a little salt in skillet to prevent sticking.
Add tomato soup and cooked vegetables.
Season meat and vegetables.
Mix and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with mashed potatoes and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Add oil, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; mix well.
Add nuts and apples.
Batter will be thick. Spread batter in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Combine pineapple and cheese.
In separate bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Stir into pineapple mixture.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp mosca
directions: In a Pyrex dish (usually 1 1/2-quart), melt butter and add the next 9 ingredients, stirring often.
Cook sauce slowly 10 to 15 minutes; do not bring to rapid boil.
Taste for seasoning.
Allow to cool slightly and then add shrimp.
(Sauce is suitable for 50 to 60 medium shrimp.)
Stir shrimp around in mixture and allow to set for at least 2 to 3 hours (preferably overnight in refrigerator).

title: red beans and rice
directions: Pick and wash beans.
Cover beans with water and let stand overnight; drain.
Put onion, celery, seasoning, bell pepper, andouille, tasso, jalapeno pepper and bay leaves in large pot. Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add more if needed.
Add enough water to cover.
Boil, then reduce heat and simmer 90 minutes to thicken.
At the end of cooking, mash a few beans.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon lush
directions: Can also use ground up graham crackers and add a little sugar.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening (let melt).
Add cold water, salt, rye flour, molasses and yeast softened in water.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Cover and let rise 2 hours.
Add 10 cups white flour.
Knead until smooth.
You may have to add more white flour. Let rise 2 hours.
Knead again and make into loaves.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 loaves.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in bowl, set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a pan and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: rouladen(german meat rolls)
directions: Spread mustard on the sliced meat.
Sprinkle with the bacon and onion. Add the dill pickle.
Roll and tie each with string. Brown rolls in a skillet, remove from pan and add flour and water to the drippings to make gravy and add a bay leaf.
Replace rolls in the pan and baste with the gravy.
Place in the oven for an hour at 325°.
Remove string before serving.
Add salt, if needed.

title: oven caramelized onions
directions: Slice tops off the onions and peel them, leaving the roots intact.
Cut each onion into eight wedges, taking care not to cut clear through to the root end.

Grease a deep baking dish. Drizzle the onions with oil and vinegar and season to taste. Cover and bake at 425° for 40 minutes until barely tender. Uncover and bake 5 to 10 minutes at 450° until soft and caramelized.
Serve warm.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and onion; cut into chunks.
Place eggs, flour, salt and baking powder into blender.
Blend until well blended. Add onion and potato chunks.
Blend only until well chopped. There should be particles of potato, not a smooth batter.
Fry by tablespoonfuls in 1/2-inch oil on both sides until crisp and brown.

title: guacamole* * * * *
directions: Sandy is a friend from Missouri and she and I cook a lot alike.
Our potato salad is almost the same as are many other dishes.
She now lives in
San Antonio and has learned many of the Tex-Mex dishes.
Since these dishes have become so popular across the country and this is so good, I just had to include it in this book.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute butter and onion. Blend in flour.
Gradually add broth, milk, salt and pepper, stirring until smooth.
Cook until thickened.
Add broccoli (puree in blender if desired) to mixture and heat 5 additional minutes.

title: the best congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple.
Refrigerate until partially congealed.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and condensed milk thoroughly.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in pecans; chill until firm.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake commercial white cake mix according to directions.
Let cool, then slice each layer to make 4 layers of cake.

title: easy salsa
directions: Wash tomatoes, peppers and cilantro. Core tomatoes.
In small saucepan, boil tomatoes and peppers until soft in just enough water to cover tomatoes, but don't let them float.
Drain half the water, then blend together with garlic clove and salt. Chop cilantro into small pieces and stir in. Enjoy.

title: cuisinart chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and place rack in middle of oven.
Have ungreased cookie sheet ready.
Insert metal blade, process egg, both sugars, shortening, butter and vanilla for 30 seconds.
Put flour, baking soda and salt in a cup and pour over sugar mixture. Put pecans over flour and then add chocolate morsels over that. Pulse twice, until the ingredients are combined.
Do not overprocess, there will be a light dusting of flour on the surface of the dough.
This will blend in easily after dough is shaped. Use rounded tablespoonful of dough to shape a 1 1/2-inch round. Arrange on cookie sheet and bake about 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Blend first six ingredients.
Add cornmeal.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° to 400° for 45 minutes.
Bread is done when toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add Ritz crackers, one at a time. Boil two minutes or until crackers are soft.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to filling.
Pour filling into a ready-made or previously made pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 300° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken with julienne vegetables
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, combine soup, milk and dried thyme. Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Add chicken and carrots. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
tags: Campbell's condensed creamy chicken mushroom soup

title: cheese ball
directions: In Pyrex bowl microwave cheeses to soften (room temperature). Mix in onion and Accent and roll in chopped nuts.
Allow to chill a couple of hours.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well; sprinkle meat with seasoned salt before mixing.
Sprinkle garlic salt on top before cooking.
Top with 3 tablespoons catsup, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon prepared mustard, mixed.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: cracker dip
directions: Cut up artichoke hearts fine.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in small casserole dish at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: crock-pot chicken divan
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly combine all ingredients except noodles.
Pour into lightly greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 9 hours (on high setting for 2 to 3 hours). Serve with hot, buttered noodles, spooning sauce over top.
Yields 4 to 6 servings (about 2 quarts).

title: orange salad
directions: Put in pan the first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil. (I do it in a double boiler.) Put in the refrigerator until set (cool). Add the Cool Whip and oranges. Beat with electric mixer.

title: mini-cheesecakes
directions: You will need 18 cupcake cups.

title: steak over rice
directions: Put steak in hot skillet and brown until done.
Remove from skillet; put on cutting board and cut into small bits.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Use 3 cups of water; put all ingredients into skillet and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add meat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook rice (Minute rice) according to the amount you want on box.
Thicken ingredients in skillet with 1 tablespoon cornstarch until the thickness you prefer.
Serve over rice.
Serves 5.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of baking pan.

title: church window candy
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and butter.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in the marshmallows and 1/4 cup nuts.
Divide mixture in half.
Shape each into a log about 1 1/2 inches in diameter and 6 inches long.
Roll logs in remaining 1/2 cup nuts.
Chill.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: turkey vegetable pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Pare, slice and pack apples in quart jars.
Cook until bubbly the following ingredients:
sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and water.
Remove the resulting syrup from the heat and add 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Pour the hot mixture over the apples, working down with dull knife to remove the air bubbles.
Seal, cook in a cold water packer for 20 minutes. 1 quart of filling makes1 (9-inch) pie or 1 (8 x 8) apple crisp.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, vanilla pie filling and pumpkin spice in bowl.
Blend with mixture for about 2 minutes.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze until firm (4 hours).

title: sunshine casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 2-quart baking dish at 350°.
Bake, uncovered.

title: poor boy casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add rest.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: On High, mix and boil for 8 to 9 minutes the water, rice and salt.
Reduce temperature to Simmer; cook 15 minutes more.
Mix the Eagle Brand milk, raisins, vanilla and beaten eggs; add to first mixture.
Remember to put just a little of the hot liquid into the cold so the eggs do not cook when poured into the hot too rapidly. Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes.
Stir; cook 2 more minutes. Stir; cook, finally, another 2 minutes.
Will not be totally set; will thicken up as it cools.
(Do not overcook as pudding.) Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: marinade for steak
directions: Mix all ingredients
and pour over meat.
Let stand overnight. Be sure to use a nonmetallic container.
Cook over charcoal.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add pineapple juice; mix until smooth.
Mix
this	with pineapple and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Layer the ingredients, beginning with the corn bread.
Mix a little dill pickle juice with the mayonnaise to suit your taste and spread the mayonnaise over the top of the salad.
You can chop a few dill pickles to put on top of the mayonnaise if you wish to.

title: deviled crab ramekins
directions: Drain crab; remove and cartilage.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Slice thinly across grain into bite-size strips.
Cook broccoli and carrots, covered in boiling water, 2 minutes; drain.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt; stir into soy sauce and sherry; set aside.
Preheat wok over high heat; add 1 tablespoon oil.

Stir-fry broccoli, carrots and onion in hot oil over high heat, about 3 minutes or until crisp and tender. Add remaining oil; stir-fry beef 2 to 3 minutes or until browned. Stir soy sauce mixture into beef; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in broccoli, carrots and onion.
Cover and cook another minute.

title: sesame seed grilled chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate 12 hours. Grill approximately 1 hour or until done. Baste with the remaining marinade.

title: tammie's lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Set aside.
Saute butter, chopped bell pepper, green onions and mushrooms.
Add to browned meat.
Add tomato sauce, chopped tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer a couple of hours.
In last 30 minutes, add red wine.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add fruit and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
When ready to serve, cut in squares and place on lettuce leaves.

title: carrot cake
directions: Measure flour; add salt, baking soda, cinnamon and set aside. Mix sugar and eggs (1 at a time); add oil.
Mixer on low speed; add dry ingredient and mix.
Add carrots.
Bake at 350° for 19 to 23 minutes depending on your oven.
Cool completely.

title: deluxe old-fashioned fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line two loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in pan.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours until done. Cool.

title: midnight scrambled eggs
directions: Heat cream cheese with butter and milk in skillet.
Stir in deviled ham and eggs.
Stir to a soft scramble.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fix vegetables according to directions. Drain and place in casserole dish.
Mix evaporated milk and soup together.
Layer in dish: vegetables, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 can onion rings, soup mixture, remaining onion rings and remaining cheese. Bake 30 to 45 minutes until bubbling.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Saute onion and add green chiles.
Drain and dice whole tomatoes and cook until most of the moisture is gone.
Add Cheddar cheese.

title: christmas holly(no-bake candy)
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in large pot.
Stir; do not let stick or scorch.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Stir in cereal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: 5-can casserole
directions: Mix together, then sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Beat egg white slightly; add water.
Beat until frothy and add pecans and stir.
In another bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add to pecan mixture.
Put into buttered pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and melted margarine.
Pat into a buttered pan.
Mix 3 eggs, softened cream cheese and sugar together.
Pour on top of first mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Will rise and fall.

title: play dough for kids
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until mixture forms a ball.
Let cool on waxed paper.
Store covered.

title: calabacitos con elote(zucchini with corn)
directions: Cook zucchini, corn, pepper, onion and garlic in 10-inch skillet over moderately high heat, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle in salt.
Stir in picante sauce and cook, stirring constantly, until most of the liquid has evaporated and vegetables are crisp-tender, about 3 or 4 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: fancy cut roshki
directions: Work flour and butter until crumbly (on board).
Add sugar and salt and crumble yeast.
Make well in center.
Drop in egg yolks. Add cream and work into soft dough.
Dough should clean board and hands.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Mix raisins and 2 cups water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer while preparing cake.
Cool slightly.
Grease and flour tube pan or loaf pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add softened margarine, 1 cup applesauce or water and raisin-water mixture.
Stir well by hand.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Candied fruits may be added at Christmastime.
Delicious and it never fails.
I like to use chopped dates.

title: potato flake cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter and add remaining ingredients. Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Form 3/4-inch balls with mix; place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Spoon into a greased 8-inch square pan and bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add cold water. Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add to jello mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add peaches.
Pour into mold. Chill.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour and milk. Pour over buttered dish.
Add warmed peaches to batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In oblong baking dish, arrange chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over chicken.

title: flounder stuffed with crab meat
directions: Score flounder. Mix crab meat, bread crumbs, lemon juice, etc., together. Fill all crevices of flounder. Spray Pam in baking dish. Bake at 350° until done.

title: cassata italian ice cream cake(take the bows and save a fortune on this one)
directions: Line a 10-inch spring-form pan with Saran Wrap.
Slice sponges in half lengthwise and place one layer on the bottom of pan. Press chocolate ice cream tightly over sponge; top with chopped cherries.
Add another layer of sponge.
Press in vanilla ice cream tightly.
Top with slivered almonds.
Top everything with another layer of sponge.
Cover with Saran and freeze at least overnight.
When ready to serve, remove from pan and frost with Cool Whip.

title: jambalaya
directions: * Can be left out.

title: warm lemon chicken salad
directions: Arrange carrot and chicken on greens.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients. Cook and stir until slightly thickened. Spoon warm dressing over chicken. Garnish as desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: possum stew
directions: Bake possum in oven for 1 hour, or until tender.
Take out of oven.
Stuff and baste; put back in oven on 1-inch board.
Take out of oven when golden brown (approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours). Throw possum in trash and eat the board.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground beef until browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in rmaining ingredients and 5 cups water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf before serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp louis dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill. Yields 3 cups.

title: layered salad
directions: Arrange in a salad bowl in layers, starting with lettuce, cucumber, onion, chestnuts, English peas and ending with cheese.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Pour in all other ingredients with juices and bring to boil.
Simmer for an hour, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese 'n' chilies oven omelets
directions: Layer Cheddar cheese, chilies and Monterey Jack cheese in lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Beat milk, flour, salt and eggs.
Pour over cheese.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until center is set and top is golden brown, about 40 minutes, before cutting.
Heat tomato sauce.
Serve with omelet.

title: very berry pie
directions: You will need measuring spoons, medium-sized saucepan, rotary beater and mixing spoons.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlic clove; add meat until browned and pour off fat.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Keep on low for at least 3 hours or on top of stove for 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until tender.
Drain thoroughly in colander.
In large skillet saute onion in 5 teaspoons of margarine until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Fold in cabbage.
Put in 2-quart ungreased baking dish.
In small skillet melt remaining margarine and add bread crumbs until brown.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spicy salad dressing
directions: Put salad dressing in bowl.
Stir in mustard and chili sauce. Add vinegar gradually; add Worcestershire and Tabasco.
Serve on asparagus garnished with strips of pimento and sieved hard-cooked egg yolk.

title: chicken or veal parmesan
directions: Dip meat in egg and then in bread crumbs (adheres better if coated a few hours prior to frying).
Fry in 1/2-inch grease. Drain.
Place in casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour off grease from pan.
To drippings, add tomato sauce and water.
Add seasonings.
Pour sauce over meat in casserole.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Uncover; top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: salmon loaf casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well and place in a greased dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Pour peaches in baking dish and mix with sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Bake 1 hour in 325° to 350° oven.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: In large glass dish, place egg and cooking oil and beat together.
Add vinegar, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning; mix well.
Add chicken, cover and marinate in refrigerator until ready to grill.
Remove chicken from sauce, draining excess sauce into bowl.
Place chicken on grill and cook, turning and basting with sauce frequently until done.

title: frozen potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes on bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix hamburger, broccoli and onion rings; pour onto potatoes.
Mix soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over beef mixture.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; top with rest of cheese and onion rings.
Bake another 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, vanilla and butter for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan; let stand for 5 minutes then sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Can be served warm or cool.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Parboil chicken; allow it to cool and then cut into bite size chunks.
Spread pieces of chicken in the bottom of a baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
In a small bowl, combine cream of chicken and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Crumble the Ritz crackers and sprinkle over chicken.
Sprinkle the poppy seed on top and then drizzle the melted margarine on top of that.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grandma nan's bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat.
Add milk, vanilla and salt. Stir well.
Break bread in 3/4-inch chunks; lay on bottom of baking dish.
Pour liquid mixture over and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until a knife comes out clean when placed in pudding.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix soda and buttermilk together before mixing them with other ingredients.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together, then add oil, buttermilk mixture and bananas.
Mix well by hand. Add nuts.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy cranberry muffins
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Stir in the nuts.
Set aside.
Combine the eggs, milk and cooking oil; add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries (chopped) and cereal flakes.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon; sprinkle atop.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: fat man's shrimp
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, mushrooms, cheese and mustard.
Heat it through.
Then add shrimp.

title: instant hot chocolate mix(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in large container. Keep tightly closed. Use 1 tablespoon per cup of hot water.

title: oyster soup
directions: *I cut oysters into smaller pieces.

title: potato soup
directions: Put
6 cups water in soup kettle; add diced potatoes, onion, celery, parsley and carrots.
Add Nature's seasoning, nutmeg, rosemary, basil and bacon drippings.
Bring to boil; cook until tender.
Use potato masher to crush vegetables, but leave some chunks.
Slowly add milk.
Add bacon.
Take some broth in bowl, add flour.
Stir until blended.
Add to soup to thicken.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix 3 minutes and bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Heat oil in covered dutch oven.
Pepper and garlic powder on all sides of roast.
Sear in oil on both sides until very dark brown. Add tomato sauce and water to top of roast.
Cut onion in chunks and add along with wine and bouillon cubes.
Cook covered on low 2-3 hours.
Remove meat and make cornstarch gravy base with 1/3 cup water.
Thicken and add kitchen Bouquet to darken.
Serve with mashed potatoes. (Can add baby carrots half way through cooking time.)

title: pat's ham salad
directions: Make
in
2 or 3 batches in food processor.
Put 1/2 or 1/3 of	the
onion
and jalapeno in processor.	With chopping blade, chop
fine.
Add
or 1/3 of the ham, cubed.
Chop fine.
Add 1/3 or 1/2 of the mustard and relish, and about 1/3 to
cup mayonnaise;
blend thoroughly.
Repeat. Then mix batches together, using enough mayonnaise to make spreadable.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix all together and add enough beer (about 3/4 can) to make consistency of light pancake batter.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake on hot griddle.
Makes 8 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 1/4 of mixture for top.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and paprika and coat chops on both sides.
Brown chops in margarine and place in 3-quart baking dish.
Cook onions and green pepper in meat drippings until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and 3/4 teaspoon salt; pour over chops.
Cover baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until chops are fork-tender.
Put chops on serving platter and put gravy that is left in saucepan.
Mix flour and water and stir into tomato mixture; cook until thickened. Pour over chops.

title: oriental salad
directions: Break up noodles (uncooked).
Mix with all remaining ingredients.

title: caramel-nut wedges
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Line a 9-inch round cake pan with foil, letting ends extend about 2-inches above pan.

title: mercy bread
directions: Cut off top of bread round. Scoop out bread. Reserve the bread. Put Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and peppers into the hole of the bread. Replace top of bread. Wrap in foil.
