Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cheese is melted. Stir several times during baking. Remove from foil. Garnish and serve. Serve with Melba rounds or bread.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cold water.
Add sour cream (blend if lumpy).
Fold until mixed.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Cream jello, cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Then add Cool Whip.
Salad can be refrigerated in bowl or frozen in 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops.
Drain.
Put in a crock-pot.
Add ketchup, barbecue sauce, brown sugar and vinegar.
Cook 4 hours.
Pork will fall off of the bone it is so tender.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Put soup meat in cold water to boil.
Put in beef bouillon. Let melt in water, then simmer tomatoes and tomato soup; cook until meat feels done.
Last thing you do is shut off soup and pour 1/2 lite cream and mix.
Cook rice when planning to eat and serve separately.
Do not put rice in pot.
Use your imagination.

title: honey bunn cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sugar and buttermilk together.
Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix together:
brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon. Pour over batter and swirl it through with a knife until sugar is dissolved.
Bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cherry jello pie
directions: Chill condensed milk.
Bring to a boil on low heat while stirring for 1 minute the pineapple, Jello and sugar.
Set aside to cool about 10 to 15 minutes.
Whip milk in a large bowl and then add the boiled mixture.
Pour into vanilla wafer or graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix Velveeta and cream cheese with hands until well blended. Add dash of garlic powder.
Mold in a ball, set in refrigerator until chilled.
Roll in chopped pecans and chives, refrigerate until ready to use.
Best taste if you make it the night before and refrigerate.

title: baked vegetarian ziti
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In nonstick skillet over medium heat, cook mushrooms and pepper 3 minutes or until soft.
In bowl, stir together next 8 ingredients.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9-inch baking dish and top with shredded cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts and mixture is heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onions. Drain. Add taco sauce and cream of mushroom soup. Cook a few minutes. Place in casserole dish. Layer beef, Doritos and cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until Doritos are golden brown.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix all, except butter and cornflakes.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix cornflakes with melted butter.
Spread on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda.
Finally add chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: trash
directions: Melt in microwave the margarine, chocolate bits and peanut butter.
In a flat pan, pour in box of Crispix.
Pour mixture over it and toss well.
Take a large plastic bag and put 1/2 box of powdered sugar in bag.
Pour Crispix in bag and pour other 1/2 box of powdered sugar on top.
Tie bag shut and roll around about 10 minutes.

title: venison hindquarter
directions: Salt, pepper and place tenderizer on a whole hindquarter (this will work as well with roast, neck, etc.).
Make a paste with hot water and onion soup mix.
Paint it over the quarter.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over the entire quarter.
Place 1 cup of water in a large pan that can be covered.
Place quarter in pan and cover.
Place in 250° oven for approximately 12 hours.
Cut in bite-size pieces and serve with barbecue sauce.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Stir in nuts.
Beat egg.
Add sugar and beat until light and creamy.
Stir vinegar into Carnation.
Add Carnation, banana and butter to egg mixture.
Stir liquid ingredients into flour mixture until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into buttered loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour. Allow 1 hour.
Allow to cool and store about 24 hours before slicing.

title: sour cream cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat sour cream to lukewarm in large saucepan.
Stir in next four ingredients until well blended.
Add egg, then yeast until dissolved.
Mix in flour, knead lightly on floured board and form into
smooth
ball.
Cover
with
damp cloth and let stand 10 minutes.
Roll 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Spread with soft butter and 1/3 cup packed brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up.
Cut
into 12 slices.
Place in greased pan and let rise. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lite pesto fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine noodles as per instructions.
Strain and toss in olive oil.
Keep at low heat.
In blender, combine basil with stock, garlic and nuts and blend until pureed.
Pour this over hot noodles and toss.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
For a heavier meal, add half and half to pesto and noodles.
Toss, then add grated Asiago cheese and toss well.
Keep on low heat.
You may also add tuna or crab.
Toss and serve.
Serves 4.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Place a thick layer of sliced apples in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon to suit your taste with dots of butter.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Add beaten egg to dry mixture until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of sliced apples and bake at 350° until brown and apples are tender. Serve with whipped topping.

title: shrimp and ham fried rice
directions: Add oil to cooked rice.
Mix well to coat completely.
Add all the other ingredients, then put in large frying pan under low heat.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Add the soy sauce and stir well.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: crunchy vegetable casserole
directions: Toss cracker crumbs in melted butter.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole and top with the butter crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in Bundt pan.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, softened margarine and pecans.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: creamed carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots. Cook, covered, in a small amount of water over medium heat until tender. Drain. In a medium size skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat. Saute onions in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and sugar; cook for 1 minute. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and starts to boil. Pour over cooked carrots and stir to coat. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes; prick with fork.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Let potatoes cool to touch.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and carefully scoop out potato pulp, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
Reserve pulp for another use.
Cut each potato shell lengthwise into 2 equal strips.
Cut strips in half crosswise.
Place potato skins, skin side down in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly-roll pan.
Brush potato skins lightly with melted margarine.
Combine Parmesan cheese and remaining ingredients in a small bowl; sprinkle mixture over potato skins.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until crisp.
Yields 56 appetizers.
Contains 13 calories.

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into balls. Place on cookie sheet. Press balls flat with a fork dipped in flour. Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven. Makes about 1 dozen.

title: joan's cuban bread
directions: In large bowl of mixer, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Heat water to 120° to 130°.
Add to flour.
Beat with regular beater until smooth for 3 minutes.
Stir in more flour (6 cups).
Put bread hook on the mixer and knead for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove the hook, cover and let rest for 40 minutes. Divide the dough into 2 equal parts.
On a floured breadboard roll out with your hand each part into a 12 x 15-inch long loaf as done for French bread.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cornmeal and place on it both loaves of bread.
Brush each loaf with water.
Using a sharp knife make 4 diagonal cuts across each loaf.
Place in a cold oven and let rest 20 minutes.
Turn on the oven to 400°
and bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
When done, remove from oven and place on cooling racks.

title: quick dish halupki
directions: In a casserole alternate layers of shredded cabbage (from medium size head).
Combine ground meat with rice, partly cooked (1/2 pound rice or more, partly cooked).
Salt and pepper to taste, use egg in the meat and rice mixture.
Mix well together meat, rice and egg.
Then put a layer of cabbage, a layer of rice and meat and continue until you use up rice and meat mixture and cabbage.
End with a layer of cabbage. Then mix tomato soup with 1/2 can water and pour over the cabbage and rice mixture.
Bake in 300° oven until done.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: finger rolls
directions: Pull biscuits apart into 4 sections.
Roll into a finger, then into butter, then into Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: race back to cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour and all ingredients together.
Cut up onion and hot pepper; add to mixture the sausage (uncooked), eggs and milk.
Bake in oven in skillet or bread pan, well-greased and floured on bottom, at 350°.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix oil, dressing mix, garlic powder, lemon pepper, dill weed real well.
Pour over crackers, mix until coated.
Pour crackers onto cookie sheet.
Put into oven at 275° for 12 to 15 minutes. Stir a couple of times.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Pour into casserole dish; dot with butter (1/2 to 1 stick) and crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in ham, cheese, onion and pepper.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry-cran-salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Stir cranberry sauce and pie filling into Jell-O.
Pour into a bowl or 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Cream the oleo.
Add sugar substitute, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Sift the flour with spices, salt and soda.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli with other ingredients, except onion rings.
Pour into greased square baking dish; top with onion rings.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg, lemon juice and water.
Mix sugar, flour and butter until it looks like crumbs.
Pat on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: old fashioned pecan pie
directions: Cook brown sugar and corn syrup slowly for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs.
When syrup cools, add mixture to eggs, stirring all the time.
Add butter, salt and nuts.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 425° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp and set aside to drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in pan.
Saute onion and cabbage in drippings until tender, stirring often.
Add salt, paprika and sour cream and stir well.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Crumble 1 slice bacon over each serving.
Serves 6.

title: children's frosting(children's recipe)
directions: Mix sugar and salt.
Stir in milk or water and vanilla.
Tint as desired and frost sugar cookies.
Decorate with M&M's.

title: steak -n- bean soup(great for low-carb dieters)
directions: Saute onions and celery in skillet with 2 Tbsp. olive oil until limp. Place in large pot which is half full of water. Bring to a boil and add frozen limas, spices, bouillon cubes and soup mix. Add more oil to skillet and pan fry steak cubes until browned and film forms on bottom of skillet. Add steak to soup pot. Pour cooking sherry in skillet to deglaze pan and add one package of mushroom gravy mix. Cook gravy one minute and add to soup pot. When green limas are almost cooked (about 25-30 minutes after adding) place other beans in pot and cook for 20-25 minutes more.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream eggs and shortening.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Will be soft.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in pineapple and bread.
Place in greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Slice chicken breasts into thin slices.
Mix sauce ingredients together and spread 1/2 with chicken slices onto soft tortillas. Fold tortillas and place in baking dish.
Spread remaining sauce on tortillas.
Sprinkle 1 cup Cheddar cheese over top of tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 stick of butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix box of cake mix according to directions on the box and pour over first layer.
Mix cream cheese, 1 stick of softened butter and powdered sugar and pour over second layer.
Do not let it touch sides of pan.
Bake for 50 minutes and enjoy!

title: apple wraps
directions: Mix well the oleo, sugar, hot water and apple pie spice.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Cook sausage and onion together and drain.
Add rice, water chestnuts and sausage with 1/2 cup water and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Add 7-Up last.
Spray 3 cake pans with Pam (bottom and sides).
Heat pans in oven just until warm.
Put cake mixture in pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool cake.

title: pizza quickies
directions: Toast bread on one side under broiler.
Place cheese on untoasted side of bread.
Cover with tomato sauce and sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Broil until lightly browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: jewish rice
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, layer the first four ingredients.
Lay stick of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Remove from oven and stir; bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: smothered steak
directions: Poach steak in wine on medium heat in skillet for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain and save wine.
Arrange steak in baking dish; add seasonings.
Saute mushrooms and onions in 2 tablespoons butter; pour over steak.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter; add sour cream, reserved wine and flour.
Mix well.
Pour over steak.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: taco bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer at least one hour.

title: vanilla never fail dessert
directions: Cream margarine, flour, sugar and coconut together.
Bake in oven at 300° for 25 minutes, stirring dark edges to center, turning over.
Cool.
Take 2/3
mixture and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: lollipops
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and 1/2 cup of water.
Cook over medium heat, without stirring, until candy thermometer registers 300° or until small amount of mixture forms hard brittle threads when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Cool mixture slightly.
Add food coloring and flavoring, blending well.
Place 24 small wooden skewers 4 inches apart on lightly oiled cookie sheets.
Drop candy mixture from tip of tablespoon over skewers to form 2 to 3-inch circles.
When lollipops have hardened, place on wax paper.
Cool completely. Store in cool, dry place.
Makes 24 lollipops.

title: white barbecue sauce
directions: In first bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
In second bowl, mix lemon juice and vinegar.
Combine the two bowls and use on chicken or any barbecued meats.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix
hamburger,
cracker
crumbs,
sausage,
milk, eggs, onions,
salt
and pepper.
Form into meat balls.
Bake at 350° for
minutes.
Turn
them over and bake 15 minutes on other side.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly until jelly melts.
Put meat balls and sauce into slow cooker or fondue pot; keep warm. Ready to serve.

title: spanish bar cake
directions: Mix by hand. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13 pan. Ice with cream cheese.

title: n. y. stuffed strip steaks
directions: Make a pocket in each steak, quite deep.
Season oysters; salt, pepper, parsley and your choice, i.e., Italian parsley, basil, touch of thyme or sage.
Sew up pockets.
Roast in a hot 400° oven for 30 minutes for very rare, longer for more done.
Check.
Slice to serve.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well. Add frozen strawberries and mix. Pour into greased and floured pans or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: crab ragtons(appetizer)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, shredding crabmeat.
Separate wraps; place 1 teaspoon of mixture on each wrap and fold like a wonton. Fry until brown in oil.

title: sarah's sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat 1 minute after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream. Add lemon and vanilla.
Chill dough several hours. Roll out on floured surface to desired thickness and cut out. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy dutch cake
directions: Sift the flour and sugar.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into small, fluted pan.
Spread some melted butter on top, then generously sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: grandma's peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients except peaches.
When it is creamy, add peaches.
Pour into baking dish, then sprinkle on top with 1 teaspoon of sugar and cinnamon.
Place into preheated oven at 350°.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes or until done.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water; drain.
Combine vegetables and bacon with sour cream.
Mix ranch dressing, mustard, and garlic; pour over salad mixture and toss gently.
Chill.
Just before serving, add nuts.

title: coconut chocolate candy
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter over low heat but do not allow to brown.
Whisk in the condensed milk, vanilla and salt. Then add the confectioners sugar, coconut and pecans.
Mix quickly; you will have to use your hands.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable spray.
Transfer the candy mixture to the pan and pat it in place firmly, using the palm of your hand to smooth the surface evenly.
Cover and store in the coldest part of your refrigerator overnight.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Cook milk, butter and sugar for 5 minutes over low heat. Remove from heat, add other ingredients.
Have Kisses and Marshmallow Creme ready.
Add vanilla and stir in Marshmallow Creme and Kisses.
Stir in nuts.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Mix the melted margarine with brown sugar, flour, oats, salt and baking powder. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and press 2/3 of the crumb mixture into pan. Set aside.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice large, peeled onions about 1/2 inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Soak rings about 15 minutes or longer in milk; drain slightly.
Beat egg and 1/2 cup fresh milk.
Roll rings in flour, then egg mixture and bread crumbs.
Gently shake and remove surplus crumbs.
Fry until golden brown in 365° oil, approximately 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for an hour.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients, except ginger ale and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Mix in the ginger ale when you are ready to serve (or if you do not want the carbonization taste, mix all ingredients and let it set overnight before serving).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put eggs, zucchini, oil and cinnamon in blender.
Add rest of ingredients and beat with mixer.
Bake in 3 bread pans.
Before putting in oven, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture on top.

title: ice cream
directions: Cook sugar, flour, eggs and milk which have been mixed until they boil.
Strain through colander into freezer can.
Add vanilla to taste, salt and Pet milk.
Fill can up with milk. Place in refrigerator until cool and freeze.
You can use fruit or chocolate to basic recipe.
You can use 2% milk to make.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, garlic and onion; add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with 6 tortillas.
Spread meat on top.
Cover with 6 tortillas.
Top with soup and milk then cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal chewies
directions: Beat together sugar, peanut butter and margarine until light and fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill dough about 1 hour.

title: steve's cowboy soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
In a large pot, add all other ingredients plus ground beef and onion.
Simmer 30 minutes. Easy and good.

title: mexicali crab egg loaf(great for brunch or breakfast)
directions: Beat eggs until frothy (about 1 minute).
Add milk and mustard, set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in crabmeat. Add cheese cubes.
Bake in uncovered 9 X 5 X 3 loaf pan at 350 degrees for 55-60 minutes.	Test with toothpick for doneness. Cool for 10-15 minutes.
Slice and top with salsa.	Slices reheats and freezes well.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain the can of pineapple and 1 can of fruit cocktail; set aside.
Blend together the undrained can of fruit cocktail and the dry pudding mix.
Add the drained fruit cocktail, pineapple, nuts, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Add coconut, if desired.
Chill until needed.

title: cabbage soup(for nonfat diets)
directions: Place all ingredients in pot.
Simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: avocado gazpacho
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except croutons. Chill thoroughly for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve in chilled bowls. Garnish with croutons.
Serves 8.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, onion, wheat flakes, milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Form into balls, using 1 tablespoon mixture for each. Arrange in shallow pan.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with egg yolk, sugar and vanilla; set aside.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package crescent rolls. Spread to fit.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over dough. Cover with second package of rolls.
Beat egg white slightly and spread over dough. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. When cool, ice with powdered sugar and water.

title: dill pickles
directions: Clean cucumbers and wash. Pack in clean jars. Add alum, dill and garlic. In a large kettle, heat the water and vinegar. Bring to a boil. Pour over cucumbers in jar. Seal and process in a hot water bath for 15 minutes
per quart.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Follow the directions on the cake mix to bake a sheet cake, a layer cake or cupcakes.
Chill the whipping cream and the contents of the frosting mix.
(Do not add any other ingredients to the frosting mix.)
When the cake is cool, whip the frosting mix and cream until stiff.
Frost cake.
Top with the cherry filling.

title: swedish meat balls in sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Simmer for 10 minutes in Sweet and Sour Sauce.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown turkey and onion until meat is no longer pink.
In large pot, combine all ingredients and stir.
Cook over medium heat until boils.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serve over hot spaghetti noodles with Parmesan cheese.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together; add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each.
Add pumpkin and stir together.
Add dry ingredients gradually and blend well.
Bake in a greased tube pan 60 to 75 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: orange chocolate cookies
directions: There is no baking powder or soda needed!

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage leaves for about 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from water and drain.
Add remaining ingredients together except tomato soup, lemon juice and sugar.
Spread leaves out and spoon 3 or 4 tablespoons mixture on each leaf.
Roll up and tuck ends inwards. Arrange in large casserole dish.
Mix soup, lemon juice and sugar. Pour evenly over each roll.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done.

title: nutmeg pound cake
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 12-cup capacity Bundt cake pan.
Combine flour, baking soda, nutmeg, salt and baking powder.
With
an electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and sugar
until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating	well after
each addition, then the vanilla.
On low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture in 3 parts, alternating with buttermilk. Spread in pan.
Bake until a toothpick stuck into the
center comes out clean.
Bake for about 45 minutes. Cool in
pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan;	cool completely.
Put the confectioners sugar on top.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake about 25 minutes.
Cool; frost with Browned Butter Frosting. Cool and cut into bars.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach; press between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Combine all the ingredients in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Transfer to a bowl.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve with low calorie crackers, pita bread or raw vegetables.
Yields 2 cups, 12 calories per tablespoon.

title: peach pie or peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into melted butter.
Don't stir.
Pour peaches and peach juice last.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Blend lemonade concentrate, crushed pineapple and strawberries in a blender (this can be prepared the night before, keep refrigerated).
Mix the blended mixture with ginger ale and orange sherbet when ready to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix cooked, mashed potatoes with milk.
Stir in flour; stir until blended.
Cook until hot and slightly thick over medium heat.
Let sit for a few minutes.
Serve sprinkled with celery seed.

title: beef and chinese cabbage
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or Dutch oven; toss in beef and brown on all sides.
Pour in 1/2 cup water; cover and cook slowly for 30 to 45 minutes until meat is tender.
Add vegetables to beef with rest of water.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Don't overcook vegetables.

title: 1000 island salad dressing
directions: Blend
all
ingredients (seasoning to taste) and chill. Sometimes I add pickle relish.

title: quick breakfast
directions: Pour corn flakes in bowl.
Add sugar.
Pour on milk.
Stir. Put bread in toaster.
After toasted, spread on butter or margarine.
Add jelly.

title: bill's chili beans
directions: Cook first three ingredients until brown in butter or oil.
Add next three ingredients and cook 10 minutes.
Make remaining ingredients into a paste and blend in.
Cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Stir often.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet; mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter rice krispie treats
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter together in large pan over very low heat.
Stir constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in Krispies and marshmallows.
Press mixture in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
(It will be easier to press into pan if your spoon has butter on it or use your fingers and butter them a little.)
Chill or set until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix above together and refrigerate for an hour.

title: yum yum balls
directions: Melt last three ingredients.
Dip frozen marshmallows into caramel, then into chopped pecans.

title: fabulous french toast
directions: Whisk together all ingredients in large bowl. Heat large nonstick skillet or griddle on medium/low heat. Add 1 tablespoon butter. Drop each bread slice in batter for 30 seconds per side. Cook each slice for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes per side (golden brown), adding additional butter as needed while cooking all slices. Dust each serving with powdered sugar. Serve with maple syrup on the side.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Split the bread lengthwise.
Brown the ground beef with the onions.
Drain the grease from the beef and add the Parmesan cheese, salt, oregano and pepper.
Add the tomato sauce or paste. Spread on the bread evenly.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Broil until the cheese melts.
Cut into crosswise servings.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: cottage cheese patties(with mushroom soup)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry until lightly browned. Serve with tomato sauce or brown egg gravy.
Serves 6.

title: play clay
directions: Simmer all ingredients in a medium pan.
Add more water and spices when needed.

title: apple pie (diabetic)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Heat until warm, but not boiling.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly, then chill.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: Lightly beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Microwave 8 to 10 minutes, until thickened.
Stir every 2 minutes.

title: sweet potato fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, butter, milk, sweet potatoes and spices; bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 228° on candy thermometer, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in butterscotch morsels.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Quickly pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan, spreading just until even.
Cool and cut into squares.
Store tightly wrapped in refrigerator.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese until soft.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla and mix until blended.
Add milk, one tablespoon at a time until desired consistency.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain. Add all other ingredients. Heat well.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix rhubarb and 1 cup sugar.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish. Combine melted butter, vanilla, eggs, flour, baking powder, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
This will be a bit soft inside.
Good served warm with maple syrup.

title: easy bread pudding
directions: Heat to scalding the milk, margarine, sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: sweet-hot salsa verde
directions: Peel the husks off the tomatillos.
Rinse tomatillos and place in a saucepan large enough to hold them in one layer.
Add water to cover.
Bring to boil and simmer until they are soft to the touch, about 5 minutes.
Drain and reserve the cooking liquid.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish or pan in oven until melted.
Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine.
Arrange pineapple on top of mixture.
Decorate with walnut halves and maraschino cherries.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except substitute pineapple juice for water. Pour cake batter over mixture already in pan.
Bake until top springs back when touched lightly in center, 45 to 55 minutes. Immediately invert pan on heatproof serving plate.
Let pan remain a few minutes.
Serve warm and if desired with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of a 9-inch baking dish.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° until Cheddar cheese is melted and mixture bubbles.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease pan with margarine.
Cut margarine into little thin chunks.
Mix pumpkin and milk and pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over and place chunks of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9-inch skillet.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and baking powder.
Pour over butter.
Top batter with fruit.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 12 or more servings.

title: cheesy chili hot dish
directions: Brown meat, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce and chili seasoning.
Add Velveeta cheese, cut into cubes.
Stir till cheese melts.
Spread 1/2 of meat mixture into bottom of a 1 1/2 to 2 quart square casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 of chips.
Add rest of meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with rest of chips, tomatoes, olives and Cheddar cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
In saucepan, put cocoa, shortening, margarine and water; bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
Mix.
Add eggs and buttermilk or sour milk. Put in greased 10 x 16-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until done at 400°.
Don't overbake.
Start preparing icing as soon as cake is in the oven.

title: sand cups
directions: Crush vanilla wafers. Pour milk into pail. Add pudding mix. Beat well with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened. Stir in whipped topping. Gradually stir in 1 cup of crushed wafers. Top with remaining crushed wafers. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Top with candy and serve.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Mix together the pineapple, eggs, sugar and flour.
Melt butter.
Tear 3 slices of bread into pieces and place in a greased casserole or round pie plate.
Drizzle butter over pieces of bread.
Add pineapple mixture; stir slightly to mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Great side dish for ham.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine and mix first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 3 ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix egg and sugar.
Add milk alternately with flour, baking powder and salt sifted together.
Let stand in greased loaf pan for 1/2 hour before baking.
Then bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 regular size loaf.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix salt and flour together.
Add eggs.
(This should be stiff.)
Roll as thin as you can.
Let dry about 1 hour on each side.
Then cut into strips.
Drop in boiling chicken broth.
Cook about 8 minutes.

title: chocolate chip whole wheat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In large mixer bowl, beat shortening mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet, flatten slightly.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: saucy beef over rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in a 14 x 20-inch Reynold's bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add undrained tomatoes, soup mix, water and pepper to bag.
Squeeze bag to mix ingredients.
Add beef strips to bag.
Turn bag to coat beef strips with sauce.
Arrange ingredients in an even layer.
Close bag with tie.
Cut 6 half inch slits on top.
Bake until beef is tender, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate dreams
directions: Melt chocolate.
Pour milk, sugar and chocolate into blender. Blend on medium-low for 50 seconds.
Spread over brownies.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Cut in squares.

title: snow ice cream(for homebound kids on a snowy day)
directions: Put milk, sweetened condensed milk, eggs and salt in a saucepan.
Mix with a wire whisk until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with the whisk, until the mixture just begins to boil.
Remove from heat; add sugar and vanilla.
Cover and cool in refrigerator.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, sift dry ingredients. Beat eggs, orange extract and salad oil together and add to dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients until blended.
Fold in strawberries and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan. Bake for 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: carrot waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in medium bowl.
Combine yogurt, mayo, orange juice and lemon rind.
Stir well; pour over carrot mixture.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: white floating soap
directions: Melt lye (not hot water).
Have grease and lye same temperature to mix.
Good dandruff shampoo.

title: janet's fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper to make a batter.
Slice green tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip in batter and fry until light brown.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain grease.
Add next 7 ingredients; simmer about 1 hour or longer.
Boil lasagne noodles until done.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan and simmer at least 2 hours.

title: corn bread cakes
directions: Put oil in your frying pan.
Let it heat up, then drop spoonfuls of batter in the pan.
Let brown.
Turn and cook about 5 to minutes, until done.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Blend crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in butter, then in the crumb mixture.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Toss mushrooms with lemon juice.
Add next 10 ingredients. Sprinkle on capers just before serving.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix first 6 ingredients, then stir in flour and salt.
Divide in half; tint one half with food coloring.
For each candy cane, shape 1 teaspoon of dough into 4-inch roll.
Roll back and forth on a lightly floured board.
Place one red strip next to a white strip side by side.
Press together lightly and twist.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Curve top down to form handle of cane.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
Cute with sprinkles!

title: shaker fish chowder
directions: Fry the salt pork (cut fine).
Add onions (minced) and fry until light yellow.
Add the potatoes (diced).
Boil fish until tender.
Add fish stock to vegetables and more boiling water if needed.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add fish and season. Before serving, add cream.
Taste is better if made early in day or day before use.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Put through food chopper.
Add 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, squeeze dry.
Add 1 quart sugar and 1 quart vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Boil 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
Let cool.
Add 1 small jar of mustard and 1 quart salad dressing.
Mix and put in jars.
Seal with wax.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in water for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes and onions very small.
Cook in water until soft; mash.
Add milk and seasonings, then put through Foley mill.
Melt butter in pan; add flour, then gradually add soup mixture.
Cook 5 minutes being careful not to scorch.
Serve with crackers or croutons.

title: lucina's oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine the oatmeal with the milk and let stand for about 5 minutes.
Add the eggs and oil to the oatmeal mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the oatmeal mixture.
Cook over medium heat.
Makes about 12 pancakes.

title: kane's pizza burgers
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet and oven capable of going to 350° Fahrenheit.

title: easy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water and shortening.
Mix with spoon until well blended.
Mix in pecans. Shape dough into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
(Pam may be used.)

title: bok choy salad
directions: Mix together in order given.
Very good.

title: pound cake
directions: Have eggs and shortening at room temperature.
Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and then one egg at a time, beating well.
Add sifted flour with baking powder and salt, added alternately with milk.
Add extracts to mixture.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes in floured tube pan.

title: devil's food drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in chocolate.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to chocolate mixture, alternately with sour cream.
Mix well and stir in the nuts.
Drop from teaspoon, 2-inches apart, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool.
Frost with Mocha Frosting:

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot on low for about 2 hours.

title: kolaches
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in milk, sugar, shortening, egg and 2 cups flour.
Mix in enough of the remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turn greased side up, cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).

title: ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, and mold in greased mold. Refrigerate till time to serve.

title: fido's favorite treats
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl combine oats, margarine and water; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in cornmeal, sugar, bouillon, milk, cheese and egg; mix well.
Add 1 cup flour at a time to cornmeal mixture; mix well after each addition. This will be a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and not sticky; (3 to 4 minutes).
Roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut with bone-shaped cookie cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheet. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely. Store loosely covered.

title: grandma taylor's fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar and milk alternately.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook about 7 minutes or until thick and creamy.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Makes three cups.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Work the first 3 ingredients together well with hands.
Take out 1/2 cup of crumbs.
Add Karo syrup and water with soda and egg.
Makes 1 pie.
Very good and moist.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat until brown.
Remove garlic.
Cook and stir rice in oil until golden, about 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth and Casera sauce. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
(Do not lift cover or stir.)
I use more than 1/4 cup sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add the next 10 ingredients to the meat; simmer, uncovered, until thick.
Discard bay leaf.
Cook the lasagne noodles in rapidly boiling salted water for about 15 minutes, until tender but not soft.
Drain.
Combine the next 7 ingredients.
Place all in the buttered casserole in the following order:
cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, noodles,
meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add milk and beaten egg, then add margarine.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
(It will be very thick and look like paste.)
Let cool.
Mix with Cool Whip and sliced bananas.

title: lentil and barley soup
directions: In a large saucepan over moderate heat, melt butter.
Add onion and celery; cook until onion is lightly browned.
Stir in bouillon, lentils, barley, carrots, salt, pepper and chicken. Bring to a boil; simmer until beans are tender.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare noodles per package directions.
Drain and rinse noodles with cold water.
Mix Ricotta, egg, parsley and 1 cup Mozzarella in bowl; set aside. Cook sausage until brown and crumbly; drain.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Spread 3 tablespoons Ricotta mixture on each noodle; top with sausage.
Roll up each noodle.
Arrange seam sides down in baking dish.
Top roll-ups with remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake loosely covered for 15 minutes.
Remove cover; bake for 10 minutes longer or until brown and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: Prepare crust.
Blend 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in chopped pecans and spoon into crust. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies and mix with melted butter.
Put into bottom of 9 x 13 pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream and mix with a handmixer until smooth.
Spread over frozen cookies and freeze again.
In a saucepan, mix milk, butter, chips and sugar over medium-high heat for 8 minutes.
Let cool at room temperature, then add vanilla. Make sure mixture is totally cool, then pour over ice cream and freeze again.
Nuts can be used between ice cream and topping.

title: cheesy hash-spinach pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of crust with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven; reduce temperature to 350°. Cook spinach according to package directions, except omit salt. Drain well, pressing out excess water.
Combine eggs, mushroom soup, flour, horseradish and mustard; stir in drained spinach. Spread hash in baked pastry shell; spoon spinach mixture over. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Combine cheese and pimiento; sprinkle over pie.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, cornstarch and salt together. Cook on top of stove until clear. Add box of jello, stir. Add strawberries, put filling in 2 cooked pie shells. Let stand in refrigerator until set. Then top with Cool Whip.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix dry dressing mix and spices with the oil.
Pour over pretzels and toss.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir and microwave one minute more.
Let stand 5 minutes and stir again. Put in container to store.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw hash browns; mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: cajun pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Clean and season pork chops with Tony's seasoning and place in bottom of casserole dish. Mix soup mix, water, rice and mushrooms together and pour on top of chops. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour. When cooked, remove pork chops and sprinkle with salt. Set aside. Add Tabasco to rice mixture and mix.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Butter cracker with peanut butter.
Top with second cracker (making like sandwich).
Melt chocolate almond bark and oil in top of double boiler or microwave (keep warm while working with it). Dip cracker sandwich into melted chocolate almond bark.
Place on waxed paper and allow to harden.
Makes about 60.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Spread creamy peanut butter generously on half the Ritz crackers, taking care to cover 1 side completely. Place the other half of crackers atop the peanut buttered ones, sandwich style. You may mix the 2 almond barks together and melt or melt each separately as desired. Using tongs, dip each cookie sandwich into melted almond bark and place immediately on waxed paper to dry. You may dip all the cookie sandwiches in 1 flavor, the mixed flavors or half 'n half for variety. When dry, remove from paper and serve or store.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice
onions into
1/4-inch
slices.
Separate
rings. Make batter from other ingredients.
Dip rings into batter and fry in electric fry pan set at 375°.

title: mammie's seafood fettucini
directions: First saute in butter onions, celery, garlic and pepper in an iron skillet. Add the flour, parsley and seafood. Cook for 10 minutes. After that, add the milk (half and half), cheese, peppers and mushrooms. Cook until all is well blended.

title: raspberry molded salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold.

title: essie's peach cobbler
directions: Can use peaches, cherries or berries. Use 1/2 to 1 cup sugar, depending on the fruit used. Add 1/4 cup water for juicier cobbler, if desired.

title: red rice
directions: Place rice in frying pan with oil or bacon fat.
Add onion and garlic, minced.
Fry 10 minutes; add rest of ingredients.
Cook slowly about 1 hour.
Add water as needed until rice is tender.

title: callie's chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, buttermilk and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Place in casserole dish.
Add remaining green beans, mushroom soup and milk.
Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise.
Lay on pan.
Mix pudding and milk. Pour pudding over Twinkies.
Slice bananas on top.
Sprinkle pineapple on top.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top. Add cherries.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat together sugar and margarine; add eggs and bananas, beating after each.
Add dry ingredients; then milk and vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 5 inch loaf pan for 50 minutes at 350° or 2 smaller pans for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Cut peaches into small pieces and add to jello.
Add peach juice and crushed pineapple and juice.
Let congeal.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on bag, then stir in beef stew.
Pour into baking dish.
On top of stew, line with slice cheese, then pour the corn bread on top of cheese.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello.
Add cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and oranges.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: french fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate over boiling water, stirring occasionally.
Remove from
heat.
Stir in milk, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Spread mixture evenly into wax paper-lined 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Turn fudge onto cutting board. Peel off paper.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 1 3/4 pounds.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup, milk, veggies (cooked) and spices in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Quarter biscuits and sprinkle on top of pan.
Bake 15 minutes or longer at 400°.

title: crab mousse
directions: Coat a 4-cup mold with cooking spray; set aside.
Sprinkle gelatin over milk in saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Add cream cheese (or Neufchatel cheese) and cook over low heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves and mixture is smooth.
Add yogurt, blend. Remove from heat.
Add crabmeat, celery, green onions, lemon juice, pepper and horseradish, blending well.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare wild rice as directed on back of box.
Add browned hamburger and both cans of soup.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: bisquick nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy pickles
directions: Empty pickles from jar and drain juice.
Slice pickles into desired thickness and return to empty gallon jar.
Pour the pound of sugar on top of the sliced pickles.
Pour entire bottle of Tabasco on top of sugar.
Put lid on the jar and let sit for several days.
You may need to shake the jar occasionally to distribute juices.
These pickles are guaranteed to make any Kittrell student smarter and better looking.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut dates and candy with kitchen shears.
Use 1/2 cup flour to coat the dates, candy and nuts.
Set aside orange slice candy, pecans, coconut and dates.
Mix butter and sugar in mixer.
Add eggs, then milk and flour.
Beat well.
Blend the fruit and nuts in dough with spoon.
Bake in a tube pan at 250° for 3 hours (about) or until done.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix and pour in an 11 x 13-inch pan the cake mix, Wesson oil, eggs, cream cheese and vanilla.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat eggs, Milnot, melted butter and vanilla.
Add to first mixture and then add the zucchini.
Pour into pie crust and bake 10 minutes at 425°. Reduce temperature to 300° and continue baking for 45 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Heat sugar, pineapple and juice.
Do not boil.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add to pineapple mixture.
Chill.
When it begins to congeal, fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate to set.

title: asparagus almondine
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving liquid.
Lay asparagus in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix soup with 1/2 cup asparagus liquid, salt and pepper; pour over asparagus.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over all.
Dot with almonds. Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: tasty rice
directions: Bring chicken broth and Cup-a-Soup to a boil.
Place rice in boiling broth and lower to a simmer.
Serve when moisture is absorbed.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve and cool Jell-O with 1 cup hot water. Soften and beat cream cheese in Jell-O until shimmery. Add tomato soup. Fold in mayonnaise. Add shrimp, onion and celery.
Mix together and mold.

title: shrimp-stuffed green peppers
directions: Place salt and garlic in a pan with water; bring to a boil. Cut tops off peppers.
Scoop out seeds and pulp.
Cook in boiling, seasoned water for 10 minutes.
Cook soup, lemon juice, black pepper, onion and 2 tablespoons of butter over low heat, stirring until butter melts.
Add shrimp, rice and parsley.
Fill peppers with shrimp mixture.
Pack grated cheese and a pat of butter on top of each.
Sprinkle peppers with paprika.
Bake in baking dish with small amount of water.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes as directed on package. Drain. Combine remaining ingredients except cracker crumbs. Pour into casserole and cover with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: thunderbird restaurant chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter and allow to cool.
Beat eggs; mix with butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese and chutney
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers to spread.
I think it is better when mixed a few hours earlier and served with finely chopped nuts on top.
Leftovers will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter.
Add this to dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture into greased pan.
Drain peaches and reserve liquid.
Chop peaches and sprinkle onto batter.
Beat together cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach liquid.
Pour this over peaches.
Combine other tablespoon sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let cool.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken, cream of mushroom, milk, rice, broccoli and 1 cup of cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top; put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.
Remove from oven; ready to serve.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar and 2 cups flour. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. While baking, prepare lemon layer. Beat eggs until fluffy. Add sugar and mix well. Add 1/2 cup flour and lemon juice and mix until blended. Pour over cookie layer and return to oven for 25 minutes or until set. Cool and cut into squares.

title: ranch ham roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix.
Add onions and mix again. Spread 3 tablespoons cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Add 2 slices of ham on each.
Roll tightly and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices.

title: pepperoni pie
directions: Chop cheeses and pepperoni.
Toss together.
Combine dry ingredients and toss with cheeses.
Beat eggs.
Combine with milk. Mix with dry ingredients until all dry ingredients are coated. Mixture will be very lumpy.
Pour into greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat over low heat.
Serve warm with chips.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into small pieces.
Put ribs in a shallow baking dish.
Start your oven at 325°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over ribs.
Bake 2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: chicken new orleans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt and pepper chicken.
In a skillet, brown chicken in butter and oil; remove from skillet. Saut onion and garlic in remaining oil and butter.
Add remaining ingredients; stir thoroughly.
Add chicken and spoon sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with long grain or wild rice.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine Rice-A-Roni with ground chuck and egg.
Shape into small meatballs.
Brown on all sides in a big skillet in a small amount of oil.
Combine contents of beef seasoning packet with 2 1/2 cups hot water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: elegant pork chops
directions: Brown chops in shortening; remove.
In the drippings, brown lightly the onion, green pepper and pineapple chunks.
Remove; return chops to the skillet and cover with onion, green pepper and pineapple.
Mix the sauce (brown sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar, catsup and oregano) and pour over all.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh tomato sauce
directions: *If plum tomatoes aren't in season, you can use 28 ounce can of whole tomatoes.

title: fish fillets and fries
directions: Layer all in long pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: flounder ala micro
directions: Scour flounder on both sides.
Place fish in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle liberally with steak seasoning.
Rub in seasoning vigorously. Place flounder in dish brown side up.
Melt margarine in cup; add 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice and Worcestershire to margarine and stir.
Pour margarine concoction over flounder. Slice bell pepper and onion and lay on top of flounder.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Cook for 11 minutes at Full power.

title: simple and delicious chili cheese dip
directions: Take knife and spread cream cheese on bottom of dinner plate. Top with chili and cover with cheese.
Microwave until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Turn plate occasionally while heating.
Serve with corn chips or your favorite dipping chip.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill all above.
Mix in punch bowl.
Add red food coloring as desired.
Stir.
Add ice and orange and lemon slices.

title: punch
directions: Pour cranberry juice into punch bowl. Add orange drink.
Float raspberry sherbet on top.
Makes 9 (1 cup) servings.

title: banana fizz
directions: Place the bananas and milk in an electric blender, cover and blend.
When the bananas and milk are thoroughly blended, add the soda and stir.
Pour into 4 (8 ounce) glasses.

title: rita's fudge
directions: Heat milk, sugar and butter and bring to boil.
After first bubbles, cook for 6 minutes.
Add the other ingredients and stir until dissolved.
Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pans and allow to harden.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Reserve one cup of strawberries for glaze.
Use remaining berries to line the pie shell.
Simmer the one cup of berries, water and cornstarch.
Add sugar.
Cook again, stirring constantly, until syrup is thick and clear.
Chill well.
Decorate with border of sweetened, whipped cream.

title: tex-mex souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat inside of 2 1/2-quart souffle dish with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.
Separate eggs, placing yolks in small bowl and whites in large bowl.
Let whites come to room temperature.
Place milk, flour and chili powder in 2-cup jar with tight-fitting lid; shake until smooth.
Pour into medium size saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat; mix in cheese until melted.
Stir in chilies, ham and egg yolks.

title: 2 layer chicken pie
directions: Remove bone and skin from chicken, cut into chunks, heat broth, soup, salt and pepper to boiling point.
Thicken with flour, mix to a smooth paste with water.
Boil until thick like gravy.
Arrange half of chicken and eggs in greased 13 x 9 x 2 dish filling 1/2 full.
Add 1/2 liquid, top with 1/2 of pastry strips.
Brown in 450° oven.
top with remaining chicken, eggs and liquid.
Cover with remaining pastry strips and bake at 350° oven for 40 minutes longer.
Yields:
10 to 12 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need 1 plastic flowerpot, 7-inches high x 8-inches diameter, plastic or silk flowers to decorate cake and plastic garden trowel to serve.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Better if made day before serving.
Especially good with apple slices.

title: munchies
directions: Melt coating.
Mix slightly with cereal mixture.
Pour on wax paper.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Put milk, margarine and sugar in large saucepan, bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, oats, vanilla, cocoa and oil; blend well.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine ingredients (keeping out 1/2 of whipping cream) in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add other half of whipping cream. Cook to the soft ball stage.
Dump over popcorn and form into balls.

title: date bars
directions: Slowly add sugar to well beaten eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Add dates, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
While warm, cut into bars and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add oil, sugars, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Add dry ingredients to chocolate mixture.
Spread in a well-greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: date nut muffins(reduced-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin cups with no-stick spray. Combine in large bowl the all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, brown sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add rest of ingredients and mix well. Serve as dip, spread on crackers or use as filling in small cream puffs.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Place steak in freezer for about 1 hour.
Remove and cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic, salt, ginger and pepper.
Saute until garlic is golden.
Add steak slices and brown lightly; remove.
Add green peppers and onion.
Saute 3 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole(for group or large family)
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix soup, sour cream, seasonings and onion.
Mix potatoes, half of cheese and soup mixture.
Put in 3-quart flat casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Continue baking 30 minutes or until medium brown.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix the first five ingredients with juices together.
Add the fresh strawberries and bananas, sliced.
Needs a lot of strawberries and bananas.

title: pineapple cream cheese cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in almond extract, pineapple, almonds and banana.

title: caesar salad
directions: Prepare Baked Croutons.
Rub large salad bowl with cut clove of garlic.
Allow a few small pieces of garlic to remain in bowl, if desired.
Mix together oil, Worcestershire sauce, salt, mustard and pepper in bowl.
Toss with romaine until leaves glisten.
Squeeze lemon over salad; toss.
Sprinkle croutons and cheese over salad, toss and serve immediately.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine melted margarine, flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk and heat slowly, stirring, until sauce thickens.
Add cheese; stir and continue to heat until cheese melts.
Combine macaroni and cheese sauce in a casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.

title: dieter's dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and puree.
Yields 3/8 cup (5 calories per serving).

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into pieces.
Put in microwave-safe dish.
Add tomatoes and jalapenos (if desired).
Microwave on High, stirring occasionally, until fuffly melted.
Serve with favorite tortilla chips.

title: grandma's homemade from scratch brownies
directions: Follow directions on side of box.

title: spicy baked beans(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in a microwave-safe dish. Cover and cook on 100% power (High) for 5 to 7 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: moonlight cornbread
directions: Grease a muffin tin for 12. Beat egg and milk, buttermilk, oil, and margarine; mix well. Add sugar, flour, and cornmeal and mix well.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain fruits and mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomato soup, seasonings and olives.
Mix well.
Turn off heat and add cheese.
Put on half buns and bake on cookie sheet for about 15 minutes at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: hot chili sauce
directions: Combine broth, vinegar and chilies.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let chilies soak 5 to 10 minutes until soft.
In blender, combine ingredients and blend until pureed.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook beef and sausage with onions and green pepper and brown. Add remaining ingredients and simmer sauce for about 2 or 3 hours. Serve over spaghetti.

title: fudge
directions: Put sugar, margarine, salt and milk in pan on stove top. Bring to boil for 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, one bag at a time, then add Marshmallow Creme.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased lipped cookie sheets. Makes 5 pounds.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and jello.
Add water.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thick and clear.
Add food coloring.
Cool.
Arrange strawberries in pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding with chocolate milk.
Remove from heat and add cake mix.
Mix in 1/2 bag of chips and nuts.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Spread batter in pan.
Top with remaining bag of chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bertha mae's pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow baking dish.
Put 1 lemon slice on each chop, then 1 teaspoon sugar on each lemon slice.
Mix ketchup with water.
Pour around chops, almost to cover.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 60 to 90 minutes until done.

title: squirrel mulligan
directions: Cook squirrels and sausage until all meat is off of the bone. Add the next 3 ingredients after meat is off of bone and cook until all ingredients are dissolved.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to suit taste.
Add corn and peas and cook for 20 minutes.
Thicken with corn meal, adding small amount as can be stirred in until Mulligan is thick.
This will serve about 8 to 10 people.

title: old fashioned pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time and stir until it forms
a ball.
Roll out on a floured surface; press into a pie pan.
If it is for a cream pie, bake at 425° for about 10 minutes or until brown.
Remember to prick the bottom and sides with a fork.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken with bay leaf and onion until done and debone. In chicken broth, boil spaghetti.
While spaghetti is cooking, saute onion, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add chicken and next 5 ingredients and simmer until spaghetti is done.
Drain spaghetti and add to chicken mixture.
Blend in cheese.
Place in casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked venison chops
directions: Soak chops in baking soda water for 2 hours.
Drain meat; season with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour, then brown in shortening.
Place chops in baking dish; put one slice onion and pepper on each chop.
Add water and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: pumpkin carrot spice layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans.

title: magic sweet potato pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl blend all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Miniature marshmallows may be placed in bottom of pie shell.

title: cream cheese bacon roll(3-ingredient recipe)
directions: Cut bacon slices in half.
Make 4 (4-inch) squares from triangular dough.
Cut each square into 6 strips.
Place each strip on a bacon half.
Cut cream cheese into 24 tiny cubes.
Put a cube on each dough strip.
Roll up both dough and bacon jelly roll style; place seam side down on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: maggie's macaroni
directions: Chop bacon in small pieces and cook on low heat for 5 minutes. Add onions, green pepper and garlic; cook until done.
When almost half done, add ground beef; cook for 5 more minutes.
Add Italian seasoning, tomatoes, ketchup and syrup.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes; stir often.
Cook macaroni by directions on box; drain.
Put in a large mixing bowl.
Add the cooled hamburger mixture; stir slightly.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Line a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish with tortilla chips; sprinkle hamburger over chips. Mix soups and Ro-Tel in a mixing bowl; pour over hamburger and chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and bake until melted.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar and oil well together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Mix in dry ingredients, starting with flour.
Mix well.
Add carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: creole pecan cheese pie
directions: Cream
together
the
cream cheese, 1 egg, 4 tablespoons sugar,
teaspoon
vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir until no lumps are left.
In
a
separate bowl beat together the corn syrup, 1 teaspoon
vanilla,
3 eggs and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour cream cheese mixture into pie shell.
Level
it
off
and
spread the chopped pecans on top.
Pour
over
the pecans the mixture from the other bowl.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Stir
Butter Buds, flour and milk together.
Heat until thickened.

Add onion and bouillon and cook until onion is done. Add cheese and enough potato flakes to make desired consistency. Add vegetables or meat, if used, and season to taste. Cook until thickened and cheese is melted.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk and cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Mix cheese and prepared macaroni in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh tangerine salad
directions: In large bowl, combine sour cream, brown sugar and tangerine peel.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve on salad greens, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, salt, sugar and Karo.
Put microwave High for 4 minutes.
Take out.
Stir and microwave again 4 minutes on High. Add to this the vanilla and butter and microwave 2 minutes on High.
Add the soda and stir gently until foamy.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let set 30 minutes.
Break and eat.

title: succotash
directions: Open and combine all vegetables in mixing bowl. Add vanilla flavoring. Mix until well blended.
Pour in large saucepan. Boil.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan or a cast-iron Dutch oven over medium heat. Add the sausage and cook for 2 minutes. Add onions, bell peppers and celery. Season with salt and cayenne to taste and saut for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden, wilted and soft. Add the rice and stir to coat evenly. Add the tomatoes with their juices, the garlic, bay leaves, water and thyme. Cover and cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes. Season shrimp with salt and cayenne in a mixing bowl. Add to mixture and cook for 10 minutes. Cook until rice is tender, liquid is absorbed and shrimp is pink. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Remove the bay leaves. Stir in the green onions and serve. Serves 6.

title: easy chicken kiev
directions: Pound chicken breasts between 2 pieces of wax paper until quite thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put a small chunk of butter, a strip of ham, a strip of cheese and a little parsley on each piece of chicken.
Fold in sides and roll up like a jelly roll. Dust with flour.
Dip in beaten egg.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Set in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before cooking. Fry in small amount of oil, just to brown. Bake at 350° for about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana berry french toast
directions: Whip eggs, milk, cinnamon and vanilla with whisk.
Use a large glass to cut circles from bread slices.
Put fruit between 2 pieces of bread (sandwich style).
Dip into egg mixture.
Fry in skillet with oil.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole dish. In a mixing bowl, combine all the ingredients, except the potato chips.
Pour this mixture into the casserole dish and top with the crushed potato chips.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers and onion in a bowl.
In a small bowl, mix the Miracle Whip, garlic powder, sugar and mustard; stir well, then mix well with cucumbers and onion.
Let it stand for an hour in refrigerator before serving.

title: anise cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy; gradually add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into half circle shape and slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: skillet corn and chicken
directions: Melt margarine in skillet, add chicken strips and cook until golden brown.
Spoon off fat, set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in skillet, heat to boiling.
Return the chicken to skillet and cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring often.

title: chapelle punch
directions: Chill, mix and serve.

title: cranberry orange spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add beaten egg.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in cranberry orange relish.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 350 about 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl.

title: almost peanut butter cups
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and spread into a lightly buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish and cover with melted chocolate.
Allow to cool and cut into squares.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix together until creamy.
Spread in large glass baking dish.
Shred lettuce and spread on top of cheese mixture.
Dice tomatoes and put on top of lettuce.
If desired, add diced peppers, diced onions, shredded cheese or mushrooms.
Dip with chips.
It's a nice colorful dish!

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, oleo or butter, 1 egg and vanilla.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Work from center and spread crust across pan.
Have sides higher around edge.
Beat together the cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°, or until brown.

title: wild berry pancakes
directions: Heat nonstick skillet or griddle over medium heat or electric griddle to 375°.
Skillet is ready when drops of water sizzle, then evaporate.

title: iced pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix until well blended.
Pour into lightly greased 17 x 11 3/4-inch baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be frosted while slightly warm.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Chop off and discard bony tip of chicken wing.
Cut remaining piece in two.
Mix all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, covered.
Remove wings and put in single layers in casserole dishes.
Baste and brown on each side for 10 minutes.

title: ham and cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients to form a ball; top with pecans.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Crumble the box of graham crackers in a mixing bowl.
Add chocolate chips, milk and butter.
Mix together well.
Put in a greased oblong cake pan.
Bake for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Sift together the flour, cocoa and salt.
Add creamy mixture and nuts to the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tests done.
Remove from oven.
Distribute marshmallows evenly on cake.
Set oven on low temperature and melt marshmallows.
Do not allow marshmallows to brown.
Remove and let cool 20 minutes.

title: nan's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and set aside.
Grate carrots and radishes (save about 5 radishes to garnish).
Dice onions, eggs and bacon.
Add all of the ingredients to potatoes; mix thoroughly.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, butter and eggs together.
Pat into well greased and floured pan (15 x 11-inch).
Batter is stiff and takes patience in spreading.
Next, combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Spread mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter; add to graham crackers to form crust.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour once, using a level cupful.
Measure and sift sugar.
Separate egg whites and measure.
Sift flour 4 more times. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Just as eggs begin to foam, add cream of tartar.
After stiff, fold in sugar, a little at a time.
In same way fold in flour.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Stir together.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup of hot water.
It's great for those cold winters.

title: good cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Melt butter.
Add the milk and butter to the mixture.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
