directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add the Italian seasoning and tomato soup.
Heat to a boil.
In a greased oblong casserole dish, spread the biscuits like pizza crust.
Lay the cheese slices on the crust.
Add ground beef mixture.
May add more cheese on top and may sprinkle crushed cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pizza casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, pepper, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add macaroni and sauce and heat mixture thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish and warm in 350° oven.
When hot, sprinkle cheese on top and bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
This recipe can be doubled.
This is a real party dish and will disappear in minutes. Enjoy!

title: chicken stir-fry(yields 3 servings)
directions: Prepare sauce and set aside.
Skin and bone chicken and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Saute in olive oil in large skillet.
Remove from pan, reserving oil and juices in pan.
Keep chicken warm. Saute vegetables in same pan with olive oil until tender-crisp. Add cooked chicken, sauce and drained pineapple chunks.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to sauce, gently stirring until thickened.
Serve over cooked rice and garnish with fried wontons.

title: green bean casserole 1
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine beans, soup, pepper, milk and 1/2 can of onions.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out and sprinkle remaining onions on top and cook for 5 minutes.

title: osgood pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix other ingredients and then fold in egg whites.
Spread over unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Make into 4 rolls.
Put on a rack in a pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly.
Add chopped nuts, dates and cherries.
Mix well.
Shape dough into balls, using 1 teaspoon of dough.
Roll in crushed cornflakes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/4 of a maraschino cherry. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tasty apple betty
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, butter and oatmeal like pie crust. Line pie pan with mixture, saving 1 cup for the top.
Boil water, sugar, cornstarch and salt together until the mixture thickens. Add vanilla and diced apples.
Pour mixture into pan lined with oatmeal mixture.
Sprinkle the top with the cup of oatmeal mixture.
Set aside.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes. Seal in sterilized jars.
Yields 6 to 8 pints.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Mix Ranch dressing, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Toss mixture into vegetables; this will thicken as it sits.
Chill.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Combine all ingredients, except chops and
oil,
in
saucepan.
Bring
to a boil.
Remove from heat. Brown chops
in hot oil in skillet.
Place in a shallow pan.
Pour sauce
over all.
Bake until tender, about 1 hour. Check occasionally
to
add
water if becoming too dry.
Baste every 15 minutes with sauce.
Good with macaroni and cheese or au gratin potatoes.

title: oyster crackers(snacks)
directions: Mix all ingredients, stir into crackers.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° on a cookie sheet.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all by hand.
Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Flatten just a little.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: fruit salad(the pie filling makes it special)
directions: Chill all ingredients together, except bananas, for a few hours; stir.
Add the bananas.
Enjoy.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-o in boiling water.
Set in refrigerator until it starts to set.
add pie filling and pineapple.
Let congeal.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Bring water and butter to a boil.
Add broccoli and cook 5 minutes.
Add rice and cover for 5 minutes, then add cream of celery soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well and bake in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free chocolate pie
directions: Mix well and pour into a graham cracker pie shell. Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add to sugar and oil; mix.
Add nuts, raisins and dates.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 large loaf pans or 5 small loaf pans.
Spray pans with Pam.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil the spaghetti; drain. Add Accent, season salt, lemon juice and oil. Marinate for at least an hour. Then add chopped onion, bell pepper, olives (all chopped), mayo and garlic salt. Better the longer it sits before serving.

title: grits souffle with caramelized onions and roasted red peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring milk to a boil in large saucepan. Stir in grits.
Reduce heat and continue stirring until mixture thickens, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, salt, cayenne and cheese.
Beat in eggs with a wire whisk.
Pour mixture into a well-buttered 21/2-quart casserole or souffle dish. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or until well puffed and golden brown.
At serving time, arrange caramelized onions and roasted peppers over hot grits.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
in
a
large
casserole. Heat in a 350° oven for about
20 to 30 minutes.
May be mixed together a day ahead and refrigerated.

title: jackie's frozen coconut cake
directions: Cook normally and cool.
Slice lengthwise.
Mix coconut, sour cream and sugar.
Take out and save 1 cup.
Use what is left to put between layers of cake. Then take about 1 small carton Cool Whip.
Mix with cup of mix and ice cake.
Wrap with Saran Wrap. Put in fridge for 3 days before eating. Very good.

title: indian tacos
directions: Top Fry Bread with chili.
Add toppings as desired to suit your taste.

title: spanish rice soup
directions: Brown rice lightly in lard.
Add onions, garlic and tomatoes. Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 3 cups of broth.
Cover and simmer on top of range 25 to 30 minutes or bake in covered casserole in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Garnish with chiles, parsley and olives. Use leftover broth, if you want a more moist rice.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine and mix well sugar and cocoa.
Then add milk and margarine.
Let come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute, remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, oatmeal, and vanilla.
Mix and drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Mix soups, onion and chicken.
Add sour cream or mayonnaise.
Place in large baking dish.
Prepare stuffing according to package.
Use the 1/2 cup butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: rhubarb strawberry crisp
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add rhubarb and strawberries; mix well.
Spoon into 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine oatmeal, brown sugar, butter, flour and cinnamon; mixing until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over fruit mixture.
Bake in preheated moderate oven, 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ramona's bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs with a fork one at a time.
Add milk, oleo, and vanilla; mix well.
Add bread.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° until knife comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.

title: 7-up party salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows in pan and cook over medium heat until marshmallows are melted.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and walnuts. Chill until partially set. Fold in Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Pour in lightly oiled dish. Refrigerate until firm.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together well and chill.
Use any fruit to dip such as pineapple, strawberries, grapes, etc.

title: avocado-cashew wreath
directions: In food processor with metal blade, mash avocados.
Remove and measure 2 cups.
Process avocado and remaining ingredients in 2 batches.
Mix well until blended.
Stir in a few drops of food coloring, if desired.
This may be refrigerated overnight in a bowl with avocado pit, covered with plastic wrap directly on spread to prevent it from darkening.
It also can be frozen!
(A real help for preparing ahead during the holidays!)
Before serving, stir well.
Spoon onto platter in the shape of a wreath.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and strips of pimento shaped like a bow.
Serve with crackers or bread rounds.
Makes 4 cups.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: spiced crackers
directions: Mix the salad dressing mix, oil and dill.
Place crackers in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour the mixture over crackers and stir well.
Place in 250° oven for 15 minutes.
Stir after 7 minutes. Cool, eat and enjoy.
These store well.

title: e z hot dogs
directions: Wrap hot dog and hot dog bun in napkin.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.

title: royal icing
directions: Combine egg whites and cream of tartar in a large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until frothy.
Gradually add sugar; mix well.
Beat for 5 to 7 minutes or until mixture is stiff.
Yield:
about 2 cups.

title: cheezy tortilla casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except tortilla chips and cheese.
Bring just to boiling point.
Place layer of chips in greased casserole.
Cover with half the meat sauce.
Add another layer of chips and half of the grated cheese.
Repeat the layers, adding cheese last.
Bake in a 375° oven about 15 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: hungarian chocolate nut torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Next, add melted chocolate, vanilla and ground walnuts.
Mix flour, salt and soda and add alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Frost with Fluffy Chocolate Frosting.

title: 7 layer overnight salad
directions: Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of sugar on top of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle one 3 ounce can Romano cheese over sugar and mayonnaise.
Cover tight and refrigerate for 12 hours. Just before serving, add 2 or 3 small sliced tomatoes, 2 sliced hard-boiled eggs and, if desired, bacon pieces (or bacon bits) and toss.
This should be made the day before serving and refrigerated.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: company slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving or make the night before.

title: pork sausage casserole
directions: Boil 7 minutes in 4 1/2 cups water the chicken noodle soup and rice.
Add pork sausage, celery, onion and green pepper.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 2 cups liquid; set aside.

title: wassail
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Makes 20 servings.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl; mix with fork.
If too stiff, add a few more drops of milk.
Knead until smooth.

title: oriental oven-fried pork chops
directions: Combine egg and soy sauce enough to cover pork chops.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf for two
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Blend egg into flaked salmon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until top is brown and crisp.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done.

title: layered ribbon jello
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and put in fridge.
Bring milk to a boil; add sugar and mix until dissolved.
Dissolve 2 envelopes Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water, then add to milk and sugar in pan.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Set aside to cool.

title: buttermilk puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in buttermilk, oil and egg with fork.
Beat until smooth.
Drop with teaspoon into hot fat (375°).
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Roll warm puffs in granulated or confectioners sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: southwest pasta
directions: Prepare macaroni
as directed on package.
Drain.
In a large skillet,
melt butter; add green pepper and onion.	Cook until tender
(do
not brown).
Add chili, corn, seasoned salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.	Stir in cooked macaroni;
top with
cheese.
Cover
and
heat on low for five minutes.

title: brownie cake
directions: Put cake mix in a large mixing bowl. In a saucepan, mix pudding with milk as directed on package.
Cook until boiling. Remove from heat and stir into dry cake mix. Stir in oil. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chips and nuts over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sinful coconut bars
directions: Melt butter in large rectangular Pyrex pan in oven.
Add crumbs evenly.
Sprinkle on nuts, bits and coconut.
Last, pour milk gently over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: inside-out caramel apples
directions: Slice apples (quarter) and core.
Mix brown sugar and cream cheese.
Spoon mixture into apple centers and dip into nuts.
Put apple together and wrap in Saran Wrap.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, sunflower seeds, raisins, bacon and onions in a large bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients and toss with broccoli mixture.
Chill until serving time.

title: easy and delicious dessert cake
directions: Spread over crust.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
You can use any other flavor of cake mix.
German chocolate is good and lemon.
Adjust to bake to your oven.
I bake mine at 250° or 275°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Peel and chop apples.
Let set in water until ready to use.
Mix eggs, sugar and oil well with vanilla.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Blend in apples, nuts and coconut.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool.
If desired, use your favorite icing.
Better if baked the day before.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix sugar, water and Jell-O; bring to a boil and set aside to cool.
In a bowl, blend until smooth the cream cheese and pineapple.
Add apricot baby food.
Fold into Jell-O mixture, then fold in container of Cool Whip.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, bell pepper, onions, sugar, salt, celery seed, carrot and vegetable oil.
Then bring to boil apple cider vinegar and pour over slaw mixture.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix together in a bowl and refrigerate.
Knead 5 minutes each day for 4 days.
On the 4th day, make 4 loaves (2 inches in diameter), 1 1/4 pounds each.
Bake on cookie sheet (a broiler pan to catch grease) on 160° for 9 hours.

title: pasta shells with chicken and broccoli
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add broccoli, onion, carrot and garlic; saute until tender-crisp, 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken, tomatoes and salt.
Heat through, about 3 minutes.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Melt butter. Add pepper and onions and simmer 5 minutes. Layer 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of onions and peppers and 1/2 of cheese. Crumble all corned beef. Repeat. Mix milk and soup and pour over casserole. Top with corn flakes (crushed). Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple and juices; add the marshmallows.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Blend into the fruit mixture and fold in the Cool Whip.

title: lollipops
directions: Grease back of cookie sheet with butter.
Arrange sucker sticks on sheet.
Cook sugar, cream of tartar and water to hard (310°).
Add flavoring and color and stir.
Pour over sticks. Wiggle each lollipop loose when set, but not cold.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars well.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon; add to margarine mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins. Mix well.

title: country style spareribs
directions: Bake ribs, covered with 2 cups water, until meat comes away from bones.
Pour on sauce and bake about an hour longer, uncovered, or until liquid disappears and the ribs are browned.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and cut potatoes when cool.
Add onion, vinegar, oil and mustard.
Toss for several minutes.
Sprinkle salt across top liberally and mix well.
Do not refrigerate! Keep on countertop in airtight containers.
Always mix well again before serving.

title: my favorite cookies
directions: Blend the brown sugar, white sugar and butter.
Add the beaten eggs.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and baking powder; add to the sugar blend.
Stir in vanilla, coconut, oatmeal, chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork and bake in 375° oven until light brown or about 10 minutes.
These should rise and fall to make a good, crisp cookie.

title: kathryn's country beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet or bottom of Dutch oven. Crumble bacon.
Add green beans; do not drain.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cook approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: peaches and cream piefort collins, colorado
directions: Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar well.
Add the vanilla and Cool Whip.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in mixing bowl, except cheese.
Pat cheese on top and bake about 1 hour at 350° in baking pan.

title: italian bread crumb breading for fish
directions: Mix all together and bread fish.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Soak dried beef for 1 minute in boiling water.
Do not salt chicken.
Grease casserole and line bottom with dried beef.
Bone each piece of chicken.
Roll meat and wrap lightly with piece of bacon.
Place in casserole and pour mixture of sour cream and soup over chicken breasts.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: In bowl, put together ingredients as listed and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in round cake or quiche pan or 8-inch square pan.

title: summer corn salad
directions: Add mayonnaise and pepper to corn, tomato (be sure and remove seed), bell pepper and onions.
Refrigerate overnight and serve cold.
Best when home grown tomatoes are in season.

title: "corn supreme"
directions: Mix corn and eggs together.
Add 1 cup cracker crumbs, milk, onions and pimientos and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Top with buttered cracker crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mushroom creamed chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts.
In skillet, melt butter. Add onions.
Add chicken and cook for 10 to 15 minutes until almost done.
Remove chicken from pan; add cream and reduce by half.
Add mushrooms and put chicken back into pan for 5 to 10 minutes until warmed through.
Serve over angel hair pasta or with vegetable.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in double boiler until thick and cool.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar to egg whites.
Continue to beat until smooth; fold in filling.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold in filling.
Roll graham crackers very fine; sprinkle on bottom of pie tins and top of filling.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.
Ritz crackers are very good used with this dip.

title: alabama quiche
directions: Place cheese, ham and onions in pie shell. Blend other ingredients, pour over cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes.

title: butter-barbecued beef loaves
directions: Combine first eight ingredients. Divide into 8 portions on double thick squares of foil.
Shape into loaves.
Top each with onion slice and 2 to 3 tablespoons Butter-Barbecue Sauce.
Bring up sides of foil; fold down onto meat in tight double folds; fold ends over and over up close to meat.
Grill 3 inches from coals 10 to 12 minutes. Turn.
Grill 10 to 12 minutes longer.

title: chicken a la maria
directions: Combine bread crumbs and cheese; reserve half for topping. Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture to coat lightly.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: "granny decie's apple dumplings"
directions: Place apples, butter, milk, sugar and cinnamon into a large pot.
Cover with cold water.
Cook at slow boil until apples are done. Turn up heat to medium, stirring often.
Tear biscuits into pieces and drop in boiling mixture.
Reduce heat to low. Stir often.
Cook until biscuits are done.

title: chili beer chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour to coat.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add chicken and 1 sliced onion.
Cook until chicken is brown on all sides. Place chicken and cooked onion in a large baking dish.
Combine beer and chili sauce.
Pour over chicken.
Place remaining sliced onion on top of chicken.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients. Form into 1-inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown. Yields 6 dozen.

title: peanut butter snack
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine, honey and brown sugar in saucepan.
Heat until smooth.
Pour over oatmeal and stir.
Turn into foil-lined pan and press down.
Let it cool.

title: pepperoni and peppers
directions: In a large skillet, saute green peppers and onions in butter until crisp-tender.
Stir in pepperoni and cook 2 minutes.
Serve over pasta or rice and top with grated cheese.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips in saucepan.
Add powdered sugar and beaten eggs.
Stir well.
Pour over marshmallows and nuts.
Mix with fork.
Shape into 2 or 3 long rolls.
Roll in coconut on wax paper.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight or until set.
Slice.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: carrot salad
directions: Soak raisins for a couple of hours in equal amounts of water or liquid of your choice.
Finely dice celery, enough to give you a good crunch.
Drain pineapple chunks.
Shred carrots.
I always need to remember there will be other foods there, too.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix as listed.
Cook at 350 degrees for 30 minutes on a greased 13x9 pan.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add the rest.
Bake 40 minutes at 325° in a casserole dish.

title: grandma vennie's basic yellow cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter, eggs and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with fruit or top with your favorite icing.

title: chicken-fried pork chops(makes 4 servings)
directions: Whip eggs with water to make egg wash.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except oil, and place on a plate.
Dip chops into egg wash, then into coating mix.
Pan-fry in peanut oil over medium heat until golden brown and done to your taste.

title: cobbler batter
directions: Melt butter and pour in baking dish.
Mix together the sugar and flour and stir in the milk.
Mix the batter well and pour into baking dish.
Pour fruit over batter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: no-bake persimmon pudding
directions: Mix pulp, sugar and whole or pieces of nuts (not ground).
Add marshmallows and crumbs from 25 graham crackers.
Make into loaf. Cover bottom and all over with the crumbs from 12 graham cracker. Makes 1 loaf.
Chill several hours.
Slice and can be served with whipped cream.
Keep remainder refrigerated.

title: flying farmer chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, salad oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt. Let stand while preparing remaining salad ingredients or refrigerate mixture overnight.
Gently toss together all ingredients.

title: cherry balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add orange juice and coconut, mixing well.
Add chopped nuts.
Mix until mixture is blended completely.
Roll each cherry in a small amount of mixture, forming a round ball with a cherry in the center.
Roll balls in cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zehnder's home style rosettes
directions: Add salt, sugar and flavoring into eggs.
Add 1/2 cup milk and all the flour, then remaining 1/2 cup milk, stirring.
Do not beat.
If foamy, let set.
Place oil and mold in fryer and heat to 385°.
Shake excess oil off iron and touch iron on paper towel to absorb oil.
Dip hot iron into batter almost to top (not over top of iron).
Place in hot oil.
When rosette holds its shape, remove iron and let rosette brown.
Turn once.
Remove rosette from oil and drain on paper towel.
Repeat.

title: coppers carrots
directions: Cook carrots just until crisp; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl; mix well.
Add carrots, and stir. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: apple crunch pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In a large bowl, combine oats, flours, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in nuts with a fork or knife.
Cut in 1 cup butter and combine until the mixture is crumbly.
Press half the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Toss apples with lemon juice and arrange neatly on top.
Dot with butter and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes or until apples soften.
Cool slightly, then spoon into bowls.

title: crescent rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
In a small saucepan, heat 1 cup of the water, milk and 1/4 cup of the butter until warm (120° to 130°).
Add to flour mixture with 1 of the eggs.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed and set aside.
In a large bowl, cut remaining 1 cup butter into remaining 4 cups flour until particles are the size of large peas. Pour the yeast mixture over the flour-butter mixture.
Stir until moist.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.

title: black olive pate
directions: Combine all except parsley in food processor.
Puree until really smooth.
Spoon into serving dish or crock, cover, chill until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with minced parsley and serve with raw veggies, sliced sourdough or French bread or crackers.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out excess water; add onion, chopped fine, and chopped water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: soft cookies
directions: Measure flour, salt, baking soda and powder in sifter.
Cream butter with sugar until well blended in large bowl.
With beater, beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour mixture alternating with sour cream.
Blend well until batter is thick and creamy.

title: ziti
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
Put hamburger in pan and brown. Pour in spaghetti sauce and heat.
Pour noodles in 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Stir in hamburger mixture; stir until noodles are covered.
Layer pepperoni on top.
Cover well with cheese.
Bake at 350° approximately 10 minutes.
Turn oven to broil and slightly brown cheese.

title: italian cheese bread
directions: Slice French bread into about 1 inch slices, cutting on an angle but don't cut all the way through the loaf.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Add 2 tablespoons salt.
Let set for 2 hours and then drain.
Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves.
Let cool. Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Then freeze.
Makes 4 pints.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage, drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat. Crock-pot works great.

title: liz's favorite potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done, but still firm.
Drain.
Toss together potatoes, cucumber chunks and salad dressing.
Serve warm, at room temperature or chilled.

title: streusel caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and egg.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar together in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once.
Stir with knife only until dough ball forms (a little more flour may be necessary).
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead gently 1/2 minute.
Pat or roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for about 15 minutes.

title: festive sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Combine juice with ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir to blend. Heat oil in wok or large skillet.
Add chicken; stir-fry 3 minutes. Remove chicken.
Add pepper and onion; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add water chestnuts and juice; mix.
Cook, stirring, until boils and thickens.
Add chicken and pineapple; heat through.
Serve over Chinese noodles.
Serves 5.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Drain and cool.
Mix in large bowl with all ingredients.
Pour dressing on just before serving.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Pound flour into both sides of meat.
Brown in the 1/3 cup fat.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Add tomato juice or tomatoes and onion slices.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
This can be cooked in the oven also, and is great cooked in a crock-pot.

title: "sugar-free" pineapple salad
directions: Mix pudding in sour cream.
Add can of pineapple and juice. Stir in coconut and vanilla (may add yellow food coloring, if desired).

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and cereal.
Drop on wax paper or pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly with mixer; beat in remaining ingredients.
Place pie shell in oven; fill with pumpkin mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Bake 45 to 50 minutes longer, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup shortening and 1 cup sugar. Add 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until fluffy. (Sugar can be brown, granulated or half and half brown and granulated.) Sift together 2 cups flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 teaspoon baking soda, and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Add this dry mixture to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Combine 2 cups finely chopped apples (about 3 average size apples), 1/2 cup chopped nuts, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, and 2 tablespoons melted butter or margarine. Pour one half of the batter into a 15 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread apple mixture over batter and cover with remaining batter. As a topping, mix enough brown sugar, chopped nuts, and cinnamon together to sprinkle over top of cake. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated grill swordfish
directions: Mix olive oil, garlic, basil, parsley and peppercorn together. Combine marinade with lemons, orange and fish in shallow dish. Coat both sides.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Put into refrigerator for several hours.
Turn 1 to 2 times.
Remove 20 minutes prior to grilling.
Preheat grill 20 minutes.
Position grill rack 5 to 6-inches above charcoals.
Set gas grill to medium heat.

title: baked stuffed clams
directions: Saute garlic, onion, parsley, oregano and the bread crumbs in olive oil for about 2 minutes, mixing thoroughly.
When onion and garlic start to brown, remove the mixture from frying pan and mix with clams, juice and salt. Spoon into shells. Sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Place on baking sheet in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until crusty on top.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Chop eggs and olives.
Mix all ingredients well; add salt to taste.

title: baked croaker
directions: Place fish in greased baking dish.
Arrange onion slices under, over and in fish.
Place approximately 1 tablespoon of butter in each fish.
Pour lemon juice into the baking dish. Sprinkle Old Bay seasoning and sugar over fish.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 servings.

title: pears
directions: Put pears into individual serving dishes.
Top with Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate sauce.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Mix ham, cheese and broccoli together.
Brush pie crust with butter.
Sprinkle broccoli, ham and cheese mixture over pie crust. Whip eggs and whipping cream together and pour over other mixture in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins, until tender.
Not mushy!
Layer in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Cut up kielbasa into slices.
Put kielbasa, ketchup, brown sugar and mustard into crock-pot.
Cook on High for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: quick summer special(punch)
directions: Add amount of water as called for on each of the cans. Sweeten to taste.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale to desired taste, about 1 pint.
Serves approximately 10.

title: corn pone
directions: Mix ingredients and boil until thick. Put in greased baking dish and brown 1 hour at 400°.

title: enormous popovers
directions: Break eggs into bowl; add milk, flour and salt.
Mix with spoon just until eggs are well blended.
Disregard lumps.
Fill 6 well-greased 5-ounce glass custard cups 3/4 full.
Set in muffin tin for easy handling.
Place in cold oven.
Set at 450° and turn on heat.
Do not open door for 1/2 hour.
Popovers should be tall and buttery brown.
Remove from oven and puncture 4 sides of neck to release steam.
Return to oven for 10 minutes with heat off to crisp.

title: easy breakfast cherry squares
directions: In bowl, cream sugar and oleo until light and fluffy.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, then add flour a little at a time.
Add lemon flavoring.
Pour into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Mark off batter into squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon of cherry pie filling into center of each square section.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. While still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: luscious jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Put 1/2 mixture in a pan and let set, then spread the sour cream over the top.
Add rest of mixture.

title: crunchy pecan ring
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter melts, stirring occasionally.
Spoon 1/4 of mixture into a lightly greased 10-inch Bundt pan.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour.
Add flour last to thicken (enough flour to thicken to bake in waffle iron; there is not a specific amount).
Bake in waffle iron until brown.
Serve with chicken and gravy.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In cold electric skillet, add the ground beef (lightly pressed to cover bottom of skillet), potatoes, onions, carrots and cabbage. Pour the soup over meat and vegetable layers.
Cover and set temperature to 375°.
When steam escapes, reduce temperature to 250° and cook for 30 minutes.

title: cherry eggs
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring occasionally, until a drop of syrup dropped into cold water forms hard ball, 252° on candy thermometer, about 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken barbecue
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Put in frying pan. Mix Coke, catsup, and mustard; pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour before removing cover to let sauce thicken.

title: curried pea salad with cashews
directions: Do not cook peas.
Run cold water over peas until defrosted. Drain well.
Add rest of ingredients.
If you are going to refrigerate very long, leave cashew nuts until ready to serve, then mix them into salad.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into loaf pan with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy quiche
directions: Grease well an oblong casserole dish or sheath cake pan well. Unroll dough and place in bottom of pan.
Brown sausage (drain well).
Sprinkle over dough.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat 4 eggs well.
Add salt, pepper and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour evenly over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: blueberry pie in a jar
directions: Put berries in jar.
Mix the other ingredients and boil until clear.
Pour over berries.
Leave 1 inch from top of jar.
Put your flats and rings on, put in canner and let the pressure come up to 5 pounds.
This is just enough to seal jars.
All you have to do when you want a pie is make 2 pie crusts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well with wire whisk until fluffy.
Add bananas, flour, salt and soda.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour mixture into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.	Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 c.
I like better than store bought.

title: chocolate delight pie
directions: Place chocolate almond bar, milk and marshmallows in top of double boiler.
Heat until the bar and marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat and cool.
Blend 1 cup frozen whipped topping into mixture.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: pigs in potatoes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Saute sausage.
Coat with potato mixture.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Dip in egg and water mixture; roll in crumbs again.
Fry in deep fat at 375° until golden brown.

title: mushroom roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, salt and mushrooms.
Unroll crescents.
Press to form perforations together to form four rectangles.
Spread filling on each rectangle and roll up jelly roll style.
Slice each roll into 6 slices and pinch together on bottom, place on greased cookie sheet, brush tops with beaten egg and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.

title: cocoa mounds
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Mix well and add mayonnaise and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, over medium heat. Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Mix everything together except noodles (may need to add a little water).
Put a layer of noodles in bottom of casserole, layer of mixture, layer of noodles,
layer of mixture, etc., ending with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked butternut squash
directions: Peel, chop and cook squash or bake unpeeled and scoop out. Mash hot squash.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Spray or oil baking dish and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually add dressing.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with relish tray of carrots, radishes, broccoli, cauliflower, celery and cucumbers.

title: quick sausage casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, mushrooms, soup and 1/2 cup cheese. Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Arrange brown and serve sausages on top of casserole.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Saut onions in grease and add potatoes, salt and water.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add soup and milk.
Serve with crumbled bacon on top. Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs; beat.
Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with pineapple and carrots.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: josie's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in the rest of the ingredients. Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Sprinkle crumbled wafers on top.
Makes a punch bowl full.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion.
Mix and bake at 300°.

title: spicy beef stir-fry
directions: Mix beef broth, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower in oil just until crisp-tender.
Add onions.
Stir-fry 2 more minutes.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Add beef, peanuts and red pepper.
Cook only until beef and peanuts are heated.

title: sausage-spice cake muffins(serves 24)
directions: Fry sausages and drain thoroughly.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add sausages to cake mix.
Bake in muffin tins in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen muffins. Delicious with fruit salads, seafood or chicken salad.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler.
Beat with mixer about 1 minute, then cook over the boiling water, beating constantly until frosting is stiff.
Remove.
Add vanilla and beat a little longer.
Cover cake.

title: navy bean and bacon soup
directions: In an 8-quart Dutch oven or large saucepot over high heat, heat beans and water to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove Dutch oven from heat.
Cover and let beans stand 1 hour.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately, about 1/3 at a time. Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: cabbage (cole) slaw
directions: Toss 5 cups finely chopped cabbage or shredded cabbage with 1 1/2 cups dressing, made from mixing and shaking the first 3 ingredients well.

title: lentil and brown rice soup(vegetarian recipe; serves 6 or more)
directions: Serve the first 6 ingredients in a soup pot and cover with 6 cups of water.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, over moderate heat for 10 minutes.
Add all of the remaining ingredients, except salt and pepper.
Simmer over low heat for 40 to 45 minutes, or until the vegetables, rice and lentils are done to your liking. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Put tomato soup (undiltued) in saucepan and let almost boil. Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to hot tomato soup and let cool.
Add other ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce with dab of mayonnaise.

title: peppermint crunch
directions: Cover a cookie sheet with wax paper.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Mix in peppermint and pour onto wax paper.
Spread into a thin layer by shaking cookie sheet or dropping cooking sheet onto counter.
Place in freezer for 5 minutes.
Break into bite-size pieces.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and mix with melted butter.
Press in pan and let set for 1 hour.
Mix softened cream cheese, softened butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Spread over crust.
Layer bananas, pineapple, strawberries and nuts.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatine in tablespoon of water.
Scald milk, then pour dissolved gelatine.
Add to egg yolks.
Pour milk mixture over yolks and sugar mixture.
Beat egg whites dry to stiff and fold into yolk mixture.
Add whipped cream and stir to keep fluffy. Arrange ladyfingers in bowl and pour mixture into the lined bowl. Cover top with whipped cream.
Can use Cool Whip.
Serves approximately 8.

title: lentil soup
directions: Sort and wash lentils well.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain and in a large pot, add all ingredients except smoked sausage and potatoes.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer, covered.
Slice sausage about 1/4-inch thick and then cut the slices in quarters.
Lightly brown in frying pan.
Drain off fat and add sausage to soup.
Simmer about 2 1/2 hours, covered. Remove bay leaf and add potatoes.
Simmer about 1 hour more.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add pumpkin.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and all spices.
Add egg and pumpkin mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix raisins and nuts into batter.
Grease and flour 2 (7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a 11 x 7-inch pan which has been greased and sprinkled with meal on bottom and sides. Shake the pan to be sure meal covers the bottom.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes or until top is brown all over.

title: shrimp butter dip
directions: Line round pan with large container sour cream.
Spread over this a medium jar of salsa (use slotted spoon).
Over this layer, put chopped onion and green pepper.
Over this layer, put shredded Mexican Velveeta cheese (large size).
Over this layer, put sliced ripe olives.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to a boil for 3 minutes. Pour over the ingredients you set aside.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edges comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: tangy orange drops
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add egg; beat well.	Blend in dry ingredients that have been mixed together.
Add
orange
juice and coconut;	mix well.
Drop by rounded
teaspoonfuls
onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat tomato soup and water until boiling.
Turn off heat. Stir in Knox gelatine and cream cheese.
Let cool.
Add mayonnaise and shrimp.
Put in mold and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash; add sour cream, soup, carrots and onion.
Add butter to crumbs.
Sprinkle 1/2 of crumbs in casserole.
Spoon squash mixture over crumbs.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: party sausage
directions: Cook jelly and mustard over low heat until hot.
Add little smokies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into buttered casserole. Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Dissolve 2 cups sugar in 2 cups water.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Will look like there is too much liquid.
Some of the liquid from canned fruit can replace part of sugar mixture. Spread 2 cups apples on dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll and cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Melt 1 stick butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Pour sugar mixture on and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Use cold stick of butter to butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer whole crackers on bottom.
Mix vanilla pudding and milk; add Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Repeat one more layer of whole crackers, then pudding.
Put a layer of crackers on top.
Pour "Topping" on top (recipe follows).

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Mix eggs, cooking oil, Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Add zucchini, cheese and onion.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: shirley's easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, extract and pie filling.
Add cake mix and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in lightly salted water.

title: turnip greens
directions: Pinch greens off stems; do not cook vein looking parts, they're bitter.
Place in a Dutch oven with 6 bacon slices or 3 ham hocks and Cajun spice to taste.
I use approximately 1/8 cup. Greens will be above lid level but will cook down to less than 1/2 pot full, don't worry.
Boil, covered, for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Combine crushed vanilla wafers and 1/2 stick melted oleo.

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and clean cucumbers. Soak in ice water overnight. Pack in quart jars. Mix the first 3 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Next, add to cucumbers in jar the next 4 ingredients. Cover with vinegar mixture. Seal and put in a water bath for 5 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cut up bacon in little pieces and brown.
Add onion, saute. Add clams, juice and all.
Add potatoes.
Simmer until tender, keep covered so juice doesn't all evaporate.
When potatoes are tender, add celery soup
and half and half.
Simmer gently, do not boil unless you like to chew on rubber erasers.
Season individually with fresh ground pepper.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients as in order.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart baking dish for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Done when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: blueberry tart
directions: Combine first 4 items and pack into long pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
After crust has cooled, spread this over crust, then spread pie filling over cream cheese and sugar.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook margarine, brown sugar and Pet milk for 3 minutes.
Take off heat and add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
If icing gets too stiff, add a little milk and keep it soft enough to spread.

title: sesame chicken
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients except chicken and liquify.
Pour over chicken and marinate 1 hour.
Put all in a shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in 9-inch spring-form pan at 450° for 10 minutes; then turn temperature to 300° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from spring-form pan, cool, top with strawberries, cherries or blueberries.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Heat broth and soup on stove top. Add chicken and vegetables. Brown bottom pie crust.
Pour ingredients into browned crust. Cover top with other crust.
Shape and pinch edges to seal.
Prick top crust.	Bake at 350° until top crust is golden brown and inside is bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Toss
peach
slices with 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.
In second bowl
combine
flour and remaining sugar; stir in milk until well blended.
Place butter in a 9-inch square pan.
Set pan
in oven; melt margarine.
Pour batter over butter.
Spoon peaches over batter
evenly.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: salmon omelet(with dairy)
directions: Drain salmon.
Saute zucchini and green onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Remove from skillet. Melt remaining butter.
Beat eggs, water and dill weed.
Cook omelet, lifting to allow uncooked eggs to flow to bottom.
When golden, spoon on vegetables and salmon. Fold omelet in half.
Slice in 2 pieces.
Serve with sour cream.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter over low heat, stirring occasionally; let cool.
Combine cream cheese with 2 tablespoons butter.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and cream until fluffy.
Blend in 1 egg and 1 tablespoon flour; add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and set aside.

title: brunch puff
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until soft.
Spread 1/2 of the bread in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the bacon (crumbled), onions and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over top layer in pan.
The casserole can be prepared to this stage in advance and stored in the refrigerator until 1 hour before serving time.
Bake in oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes until set and puffed.
Makes 8 servings.

title: company chicken
directions: Oil flat casserole well.
Place small amount of soup in casserole.
Place rice evenly over soup.
Place seasoned chicken on top (pepper and garlic salt on each piece).
Lay chopped green chilies on chicken.
Pour remaining soups and 1/2 cup milk (mixed) over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Stir 2 heaping teaspoonfuls into each cup of hot water.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix oil, sugar, molasses and egg.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and spices.
Divide dough in half.
Shape 1/2 into 2 strips about 15 x 3-inches about 3 inches apart on cookie sheet (lightly greased).
Sprinkle each strip with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Bake at 375° until edges are light brown and tops begin to crack, 6 to 7 minutes for soft cookies, 8 to 9 minutes for crisp.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Cut each strip crosswise into 1-inch slices.
Repeat with remaining half of dough.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: sherried sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix soup, sour cream and carrots together and add to squash.
Stir butter and stuffing mix together until all butter is absorbed. Spread half of stuffing mix in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour squash mixture over it.
Top with remaining stuffing. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco with milk.
Add 1 pound sugar; mix well.
Stir in cocoa and remaining 1 pound sugar and add to first mixture.
Add vanilla and beat thoroughly.
This is enough for 2 cakes and can be refrigerated for some time.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Skin chicken breasts and halve lengthwise.
Arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a mixing bowl, combine apricot pie filling, lemon juice, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in pecans.
Pour apricot mixture over chicken pieces; cover and bake in a 375° oven for 55 to 60 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Arrange chicken on rice; spoon apricot mixture on top.
Serves 6.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg in a bowl; blend until stiff.
Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in extra sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately top each cookie with chocolate kiss; pressing down firmly so cookies cracks around edges, remove from cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: easy chocolate souffle
directions: Note: You can make the souffle batter the day before you serve it, and put it in the refrigerator overnight - cold batter is easier to work with; however, you can also make the batter and refrigerate it for only 1-2 hours.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the rhubarb.
Pour half of the batter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with rhubarb and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Put over batter and then add remaining batter.
Bake until batter and rhubarb are done. Bake at 350°.

title: microwave quickie fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in a mixing bowl.
Pour in milk and place margarine on top.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir with a wooden spoon until ingredients are blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch buttered pan. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut and serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In the bottom of a casserole dish, slice 1 onion and 1 potato. Top with pork chops.
Mix together the soups; pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Layer spaghetti noodles, chicken, mushrooms and spaghetti, then top with sauce.

title: grandma freemon's bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs until mixed, then add sugar, vanilla, salt, and nutmeg.
Stir in milk and mix well.
Put bread pieces in bowl and pour milk mixture over bread.
Bake about 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
It is done when knife comes out of center clean.
It will puff up but will go down when out of the oven.
Serve with caramel sauce over the top.

title: pie crust
directions: Using a pastry blender, blend flour, salt and Crisco until the mixture is the size of small peas.
Add the cold water and mix until it cleans the sides of the bowl.
Divide the dough in half and roll thin on a lightly floured table.
Use one on the bottom of the pan and slit the top one to allow steam to escape.
It's a good idea to place a pizza pan on the rack below to catch drippings. This saves oven cleaning.
This makes 2 crusts.

title: macaroni and gar salad
directions: Mix cooked cold gar with macaroni.
Add carrots, celery, red onions and cabbage.
Toss this mixture with mayonnaise, parsley, dill and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill and serve on a bed of cold lettuce.

title: river slaw
directions: Mix ingredients and serve!

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until lumps are done.
Put in pan (8-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until done.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Beat the cream cheese.
Add all ingredients except paprika. Put in buttered casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through.

title: cherry dessert supreme
directions: Mix well with hand.
Spray 8 x 11-inch Pyrex with Pam.
Press into dish.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes; cool.

title: lasagne with meat sauce
directions: Saute in oil the onion and garlic.
Add sausages and ground chuck and brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook lasagne noodles.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces.
Fry bacon crisp.
Add cabbage, salt and onion.
Fry until tender.
Stir often.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Put in large casserole dish.
Mix butter and tomato sauce with macaroni.
Cut Velveeta in chunks and mix together.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese melts thoroughly.

title: sandra's pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onion and sweet pepper in jar or other container with lid.
Sprinkle with salt and stir.
Let stand in refrigerator 2 hours.
Take out; drain liquid and add sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Stir.
Put back in refrigerator.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Stir in eggs, margarine, pineapple, coconut and milk.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Add meat, eggs and enough bread crumbs so that meat mixture barely sticks together.
Cut up small piece of garlic in a skillet that has enough olive oil to cover bottom of skillet.
Shape balls and put in olive oil to brown on all sides.
Sprinkle oregano and basil over meat.
Take up meatballs and put in another pot.
Add 2 cans of tomato paste to olive oil.
Let cook for 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
Pour in the pot with meatballs.
Add enough water to cover meatballs.
Cover and bring to boil and then turn heat down as low as possible.
Let simmer 4 hours.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender in boiling water and drain.
Brown ground beef until done.
Mix all ingredients together.
If desired, cheese may be cut into small squares and mixed with other ingredients.
Place in 350° oven until heated through.
Grate cheese on top and return to oven until melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: mary virginia's pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Press into pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in small amount of oil.
Put in pan the sausage; turn and stir to light brown (about 10 minutes). Pour off grease.
Put in the tomato sauce, garlic powder, chili powder and chili hot red beans.
Bring to boil.
Cut down to simmer for about 30 minutes.
Pour over rice when ready to eat.

title: barbecue redfish
directions: On stove, saute onion and garlic in butter. Add barbecue sauce. Season with
Tony's, garlic powder, salt, red pepper and lemon pepper.
Season redfish with lemon juice and Tony's prior to placing on grill.
Place fish on scale side on grill. Baste fish periodically with barbecue sauce mixture.
Leave on grill for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour boiling water over margarine in a mixing bowl; stir in sugar, cereal and salt.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Beat eggs and add to cereal mixture.
Mix in flour one cup at a time until stiff dough is formed.
Turn into greased bowl and brush top with melted butter.
Cover and let rise 2 hours in a warm place.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Cover and let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: vegetables in cheese sauce
directions: In 3-quart micro-safe casserole. Stir soup until smooth.
Stir in milk, basil and garlic.
Mix well.
Add vegetables and stir to coat well.
Cover with lid.
Microwave on High 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: truffle
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Before cake is cool, break it into 3, using a spoon.
In a clear glass bowl, follow these steps:
Spread cake mixture, then 1 tablespoon Kahlua, then 1 box pudding and then Cool Whip.
Repeat these steps 3 times. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Combine milk, egg and oil and add to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Toss together blueberries and 2 tablespoons sugar; fold into batter along with lemon rind.
Bake in greased muffin pan about 25 minutes at 400°.
While still warm, dip in melted oleo and sprinkle with sugar.

title: happy valley cake(no egg)
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into ungreased 8-inch pan.
Stir a little, then make 3 wells in dry mixture.
Put in, one at a time, the oil, vanilla, vinegar and cold water.
Stir together with slotted spoon until well blended.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: luscious overnight salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt, vinegar, pineapple syrup and butter. Cook all together in a double boiler until thick.
Stir constantly. Cool.

title: grilled corn
directions: Preheat your barbecue grill.
Peel away outer husk, but do not remove.
Remove silky threads and wrap outer husk back around the ear.
Soak corn in water for 15 to 30 minutes.
Place corn on grill for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove corn from grill; remove husk. Brush with butter and season with salt and pepper.
Roll the husked, buttered corn on the grill for a minute or 2.
Makes 6 servings, 2 ears each.

title: mexican relish
directions: Grind the first 5 ingredients; combine with the salt.
Mix well.
Put in a bag and drain overnight.
Chop the celery.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine
potatoes,
cup
butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir in remaining butter.
Place in baking dish. Crush
corn
flakes
and
sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake
at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with a lemon twist and parsley if desired.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: date and apricot bars
directions: Mix together in saucepan the first 4 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, until thickened (5 minutes).
Cool. For crust, mix together thoroughly the shortening and brown sugar. Sift together and stir in flour, soda, salt, oats and vanilla. Mix thoroughly using hands.
Press 1/2 of this crumb mixture in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with cooled filling. Cover with remaining mix.
Pat lightly.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. While warm, cut in bars and remove from pan.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients (except oleo)
well. Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips or cornflakes (optional).
Drizzle 1/2 cup oleo over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken picante
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix together picante sauce, brown sugar and dijon mustard.
Place chicken baking dish.
Pour picante sauce mixture on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Serves:

title: coney island casserole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add franks and brown on all sides, turning frequently.
Remove and set aside.
Add beef to drippings and stir constantly, until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in browned franks.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup olives.
Add cooked macaroni to meat sauce mixture and toss lightly until combined.
Season to taste.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; drain.
Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add pizza sauce, Mozzarella cheese and hamburger to noodles.
Spread in dish.
Top with pepperoni, sausage and 1 cup of each cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: gilroy garlic bread
directions: Thoroughly combine first 6 ingredients in medium bowl. Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread garlic butter on cut sides of bread. Wrap each bread half in foil.
Place bread on baking sheet, cut side up.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove foil from bread.
Preheat broiler.
Broil cut side up until golden brown, about 2 minutes.

title: four-fruit cooler
directions: Thaw raspberries, peaches and lemonade.
In a blender, combine raspberries, peaches, lemonade, bananas and 1/2 cup cold water. Blend until smooth.
Transfer mixture into pitcher and add 2 cups cold water; stir.
Serve immediately over ice or chill in refrigerator for several hours.
Stir before serving.

title: country ham
directions: Place sweet potatoes in the crock-pot to form rack.
Put the ham on top of the potatoes.
In a bowl, mix sugar, mustard and a little pineapple juice.
Pour over ham along with the rest of the pineapple.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Sift flour, then measure. In a separate bowl, pour hot water over sugar, salt and butter; stir until butter is melted. In a small bowl, dissolve the yeast in the 2 tablespoons warm water and add to the butter mixture. Add 1 cup flour, gradually beating until smooth. Add egg and remaining flour to make a soft dough. Put in refrigerator for several hours or overnight. Take out; press down to release air. Shape into walnut size balls. Put in pan and place in a warm place until they are doubled in size. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: pineapple supreme
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and mix with mixer for 10 minutes.
Bake at 300 for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours in well greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.

title: onion rings
directions: Optional additions to Herman: Before baking, you can add raisins, nuts, dried fruits, apples, blueberries, etc.

title: hearty fiesta burgers
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, eggs, onion, worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Add ground beef & mix well. Shape meat mixture into patties. In large skillet, brown patties on both sides. Pour soup over meat; top with beans & green peppers. Cook, covered, over low heat for 10 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over mixture; cover & cook 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: grandmother's taffy
directions: Cook molasses, sugar and vinegar for 10 minutes.
Add baking soda just before removing from stove.
Pour onto greased platter. Cool until you can handle, then pull.
Cut into pieces with shears.
Cool dry weather is best time to make taffy.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in water on top of stove. Crumble cream cheese and add to jello mixture.
Let this simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add pineapple (juice also). Pour into mold or dish.
Add chopped pecans on top and chill.

title: chocolate-pecan-fudge pie
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/3 cup melted butter; press firmly on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: avocado bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and allspice.
Combine eggs, then dry ingredients, nuts and avocado.
Bake in two 8-inch loaf pans or 3 baby loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Beat the butter and sugar to a cream.
Add the beaten yolks of the eggs, then the pineapple and cream, and lastly, the beaten egg whites whipped in lightly.
Bake with an under crust only.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix gelatine with 1 cup cold water and 1 cup hot water.
Add pineapple juice and all; let congeal.
After congealed, beat Dream Whip stiff (3 boxes).
Then add to jello mix.
Take 1/2 mix, put in the bottom of pan.
Then cut cake or break up in small pieces and add on top of mix.
Then add the other 1/2 of mix; now beat other box of Dream Whip and add to top of mix.
Add coconut, nuts (if desired), or cherries.
Will keep in fridge for 3 weeks.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large dish and moisten with mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Mix butter, milk and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and walnuts. Mix well and drop from spoon onto a cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine water and both sugars in saucepan.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add coffee.
Cool.
Stir in vodka and vanilla. Pour in screw top jar and let stand for 2 weeks at room temperature.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and hard-boiled eggs.
Mash potatoes and eggs together.
Add salt, sugar, onion (optional), vinegar and mayonnaise.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve hot or cold on lettuce with sliced eggs.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Put ginger ale in just before serving and keep mixture stirred while serving.
This recipe makes 4 gallons and serves 160 to 175 people.

title: tabooley(arabic salad)
directions: Cover cracked wheat with water and let soak while preparing vegetables.
Chop all vegetables fine.
Use only the leaves of the parsley and fresh mint.
Drain and squeeze the water out of the cracked wheat and add to the veggies.
Add the remaining ingredients, adjusting seasoning to taste.
Serve with fresh pita bread.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, lemon juice, curry powder and mayonnaise. Layer rice in bottom of
9 x 13 inch baking dish; add broccoli, chicken and pour soup mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt eva's brownies
directions: Melt together shortening and chocolate.
Beat together the eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add melted mixture to beaten mixture and beat well.
Add flour and mix.
Mix in nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine
thawed
apple juice and cornstarch in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add margarine and spices, mixing well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon mixture into the pie
shell and place the crust on top.
Cut slits in the crust to
allow steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° for another 30 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal bread(recipe is for a 1 pound bread maker)
directions: Place all ingredients in bread pan, select light crust setting and press start.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together (do not beat).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
Remove from burner and pour over slightly crushed noodles and nuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper or foil and refrigerate to cool 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour all in casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Whip until
foamy
the egg white and water.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and
salt.
Add
1 pound pecans to whipped egg whites and thoroughly
coat.
Add sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Totally coat pecans.
Put
in well greased cookie sheet or shallow pan and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: crabbies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add can of crabmeat.
Spread on English muffin and place under broiler or until cheese bubbles and browns lightly.

title: spanish paella
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven; brown chicken.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Drain off fat.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion, tomatoes and seasonings in Dutch oven until onion is tender (5 minutes).
Stir in rice and broth; heat to boiling.
Add chicken. Cover and bake 35 minutes.
Add shrimp and peas.
Bake until chicken is tender (10 minutes).
Serve in paella pan or shallow serving dish.
Garnish with pimento strips, parsley and artichoke hearts.

title: mell's reuben dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes in covered casserole dish.
Remove cover and bake an additional 5 minutes, until it begins to turn golden brown around edges.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil your chicken, break into bite size pieces and set it aside.
Melt butter in a large pot (4 or 5-quart).
Add celery, bell pepper, yellow onions and garlic; cook until tender.
Add green onions and cook for 5 minutes more.
Add both cans of soup and chicken pieces; cook for about 10 minutes.
Add rice, salt and pepper and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until top is golden.

title: broccoli casserole no. 2
directions: Put broccoli in casserole.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix soup, milk and grated cheese.
Blend well.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Slice ripe peaches into baked pie shell.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, salt and water until clear, stirring all the time. Add jello.
Cool.
Pour over peaches and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: orange beets
directions: Moisten cornstarch with 1/2 of water.
Mix other ingredients (except butter and beets).
Bring to a boil; add cornstarch. Stir and cook until clear and thick (about 8 minutes).
Add butter, then beets.
Heat well and serve.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain thoroughly.
Set aside.
Spray skillet with butter flavored cooking spray.
Brown the diced onion.
Add cooked ground beef.
Stir refried beans into beef mixture.

title: carol's broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onions in 4 Tbsp. of the butter. Add flour and water. When thick, add cheese. Combine sauce with broccoli, add eggs. Pour into greased casserole dish and top with buttered cracker crumbs, using remaining 2 Tbsp. of butter.
Bake 45-50 minutes at 350°.

title: hot sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Cook and drain loose sausage.
Spoon into large bowl.
Cool completely.
Add cheese, Bisquick and water.
Mix until blended. Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 48.

title: five bean casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake at 300° uncovered for 2 hours.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Partially boil carrots, onion and celery in small amount of water; drain.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugars, egg and water.
Add vanilla.
Next, add all dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal.
Next, add raisins and chopped almonds. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1/2 of the strawberries; add cornstarch and sugar.
Cook until clear.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cool; add whole berries.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Garnish with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix.
Top with favorite topping.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook, drain and set bacon aside to use as garnish. Cook diced potatoes and onion in water until soft.
Allow to cool a few minutes then add remaining ingredients, except bacon and corn. Add corn during last ten minutes of cooking.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Takes about 2 hours to prepare.
Delicious on a cold night!

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain liquid from pickles and fill jar with sugar.
Let stand in
refrigerator
overnight.
Sugar
will
make juice in pickles again and
you
will have a crisp, sweet pickle with a little different taste.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix butter and cheese well.
Add flour and mix.
Then add Rice Krispies to form soft, firm dough.
Add few drops of Tabasco and mix well.
Make the dough into very small balls.
Place on cookie sheets and flatten with damp fork.
Cook in 275° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in tube pan; set in cold oven and turn heat up to 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pina colada bars
directions: Gently mix whipped topping with softened cream cheese. Add sugar and flavoring. Mix until smooth. Add pineapple and coconut. Place in container of desired depth and freeze for about 2 1/2 hours. Cut into bars and serve.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Melt butter in a large saucepan; remove from heat.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Gently toss in nuts. Place seasoned nuts in a single layer in a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes, turning frequently, until browned and crisp.
Store, tightly sealed, in the refrigerator.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: In a bowl, combine first six ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with vegetables.

title: chess cake
directions: Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Beat together cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and onion.
Roll bread paper thin between wax paper with rolling pin.
Place 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture on each slice, spread and roll up. Cut in half.
Roll in melted butter.
Place on wax paper, seam side down, for half an hour to absorb butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve warm.
Makes 28.
Can be used as an appetizer or a sandwich.

title: iowa ham balls
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Using a 1/3 measuring cup, shape mixture into 2-inch balls.
Place in 2 large shallow roasting pans.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over balls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, basting frequently with sauce.

title: chicken pilau
directions: In a 10 inch skillet, over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp, set aside. Spoon off all but about 2 Tbsp. drippings. In hot drippings, saute onion and garlic until tender; add raw rice and cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Add broth, tomatoes, ground red pepper, and chicken.
