Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add green pepper and cook 2 minutes more. Remove from heat; let stand covered for 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Garnish with bacon. Serves 4.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Heat oil in an iron skillet until very hot.
Add half the mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and peppers.
Pour on remaining mixture.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into 1-inch balls and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg, vanilla and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients and fold in zucchini.
Grease and flour oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Icing is optional.
Very moist.

title: cheese-stuffed shells
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain. Transfer to a large bowl. Stir in the spinach, cream cheese and egg. Add 1 cup Mozzarella, Cheddar, cottage cheese, Parmesan, salt, pepper and cinnamon. Mix well. Stuff shells and arrange in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine sauce ingredients; mix well. Spoon over shells.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender to mix. Pour in pie shells. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
In saucepan, melt margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla, cinnamon and soda.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 34 minutes.
Pour icing over hot cake.

title: flowerpot dirt cake
directions: You will need one new flowerpot (8 x 10-inch) and silk flowers.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and ice.
Let drain overnight in colander in a pillow case.
Rinse with cold water, 2 or 3 times, in the a.m. and let drain for 1/2 hour.

title: easiest flan
directions: Melt 1 cup white sugar and coat bottom and sides of baking dish.
Mix milk, cream, eggs and vanilla.
Pour mix into coated dish.
Place in pan of water; bake at 325° for 1 hour or until center is firm.
Invert onto platter.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, layer ingredients in order.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours.
Toss lightly at the table.
Good!

title: russian sour cream salad
directions: Shred lettuce by hand . Add cut-up scallions (both bulb and green stem), peeled cucumber sliced crosswise, sliced radishes, 1 tablespoon of the minced fresh or dried bay dill weed, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Last of all, add the sour cream and the juice of the lemon.
Mix and sprinkle with the remaining tablespoon of minced dill.
Serve immediately so that the sour cream does not get watery.

title: oriental beef and vegetables
directions: Combine beef, green pepper, mushrooms, water chestnuts, onion and garlic.
Stir-fry for about 5 minutes, stirring continuously, using 2 tablespoons oil.

title: fresh veggie salad
directions: Cook and cool noodles.
Then add all your veggies in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Add dressing.
Mix well.
Will keep in refrigerator for long time.
Very low calories.
Serve with lemon pepper.

title: country biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or knife until mixture is fine crumbs.
Mix well and roll out to 1/2-inch thick.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Press firmly into bread loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: curried chicken and broccoli
directions: Line casserole dish with thawed broccoli and arrange chicken over it.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and spread over the top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion and saute until softened.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Remove pan from heat and stir in buttermilk.
Return to heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, mustard and salt.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add red pepper.

title: salmon corn soup
directions: Cook celery, garlic and onion in 1/2 cup of broth.
Add potatoes, carrots and remaining broth.
Simmer 30 minutes until tender.
Add broccoli and cook 5 minutes more.
Add salmon, corn and milk.
Heat briefly.

title: carob treats dog biscuit
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until blended.
Dough will be stiff.
Chill. Roll dough on a greased cookie pan and cut into shapes, 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: Preheat griddle or skillet.
Spray with Pam.
Mix eggs, milk, cinnamon and sugar together.
Dip slice of bread into mixture. Place on griddle and brown.
Serve with fruit of choice and/or syrup.

title: low-fat mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Mash potatoes, then whip with electric mixer.
Fold in mushroom soup, adding a little skim milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked potato and fried chicken
directions: Place butter inside baked potatoes. Add cut up chicken strips. Mix gravy according to package directions. Pour over chicken. Top with cheese.

title: snow candy divinity
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, corn syrup, water and salt. Boil to medium-ball stage (240°). Pour about half of mixture slowly over the stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly. Cook remaining syrup mixture to very hard-ball stage (265°). Beat syrup mixture into egg whites and continue to beat until mixture holds its shape. Add vanilla and nuts. Drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Makes 5 to 6 dozen pieces of divinity.

title: bread bowl salad bowls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scratch dough should be allowed to rise once before making the bread bowls.
Also, the store-bought dough should rise once before forming the bowls.

title: colorado fudge
directions: In small pan, caramelize 2 cups of white sugar.
In a large kettle, mix 4 cups white sugar, milk and butter.
Let this mixture come to a boil, stirring constantly while the sugar is caramelizing. Pour caramelized mixture into creamed mixture.
Cook to hard boil stage.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Beat in thoroughly and let set 20 minutes.
Add walnuts and pecan halves. Beat until thick enough to spread.
Cool and eat!
Gain!
Gain! Gain!

title: easy butterscotch pralines
directions: Mix pudding mix, white sugar, brown sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Add pecans; boil 2 to 5 minutes or until soft ball stage.
Beat until shiny.
Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl.
Combine well beaten eggs, buttermilk and melted shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until flour is barely moistened (disregard lumps in batter; overstirring makes less tender pancakes).
Drop batter on hot, lightly greased griddle or frying pan; turn cakes when they are golden brown and bubbles on surface break.
Makes about 18 pancakes.

title: chocolate lovers bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder and cocoa; mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Put marshmallows on top of hot bars.
Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and stir in Rice Krispies.
Put on top of marshmallows.
Chill and cut in squares.

title: bavarian walnut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in mixing bowl with electric mixer. Beat in vanilla.
Using low speed, mix in flour.
Then add 1/2 cup walnuts.
With lightly floured hands, shape dough into a roll 2 inches in diameter.
Roll in remaining walnuts to coat.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Slice dough 1/4-inch thick. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Transfer to rack to cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Pour in oil and mix at medium speed until there is no visible trace of oil.
You must mix it at least three minutes.
Add the flour and spices.
Then add the pumpkin and mix at a slower speed until the batter is well blended.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar, unsulphured molasses and egg.
Sift together nonfat skim milk, flour, spices, salt, soda and baking powder; stir into the creamed mixture.
Add grated carrots, raisins and rolled oats; mix well.
Drop by level tablespoons on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: pistolettos
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together, drain.
Mix in cheese until melted and then add cooked rice and broccoli (broken into small pieces). Cut top off of roll and pull out inside.
Fill with mixture (one to two tablespoons).
Replace top of roll.
May be wrapped separately and stored in freezer until ready for use. Take out, thaw and brush with garlic butter.
Place in oven on 350° or until brown.
Temperature determined on individual oven. When wrapped individually, you can take out as many as needed. Filling makes about 21 rolls.

title: blitz torte
directions: Make a batter of the butter, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, egg yolks, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Spread this in bottom of 1 coffee cake tin.
Beat the two egg whites until stiff; add 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread this over the batter.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake about 1/2 hour at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: jean's cheese balls
directions: Place first five ingredients in food processor and process until creamy.
Divide in thirds and shape first piece into a smooth ball.
Roll in dill weed or lemon pepper.

title: enchilada
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt, pepper, and garlic salt.
(Save enough cheese to cover top.)
Set aside.

title: kentucky kahlua
directions: Boil water and sugar, then reduce heat.
Allow to simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla beans.
Let stand until cold.
Add coffee and vodka to sugar mixture.
Place in 1/2 gallon jar.
Cover well and let stand for at least 2 weeks.
Remove vanilla beans and serve.

title: peas continental
directions: In a skillet, melt butter and saute mushrooms with onion until onion is tender.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, marjoram and sherry.
Toss with hot peas. Serves 4.

title: diabetic applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine, egg, vanilla, and sugar until fluffy. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with applesauce. Stir in walnuts. Spoon into cupcake tins and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add 2 eggs, blending well.
Then add 2 more eggs and half the flour, then the 2 remaining eggs.
Add rest of flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 300° for 70 minutes.

title: becky's sad cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; beat mix with a fork.
(Don't use an electric mixer.)
Add Bisquick mix, coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased baking pan and bake at 325° until toothpick is still sticky, about 25 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs and sugar in a large bowl.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and spread over top.
Cool and cut into squares.
Keep refrigerated!

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Chill and serve in lettuce cups.

title: easy pineapple danish
directions: In smal bowl combine yogurt, sugar and vanilla; set aside. Brush 1 side of each slice of bread with half of the margarine. Place bread, margarine side up, on baking sheet.
Broil until bread is lightly browned, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread each bread slice with 1/2 cup pineapple and continue broiling until pineapple is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Top each Danish with half of the yogurt mixture, serve immediately.

title: cranberry-yogurt parfaits
directions: Place about 2 tablespoons cranberry sauce in bottom of 4 parfait glasses.
Layer yogurt, remaining cranberry sauce and top with granola.
Makes 4 servings.

title: layered mixed vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl or 13 x 9-inch pan, layer lettuce and onion. Spoon 1/2 cup mayo evenly over top.
Layer celery, green pepper and peas.
Spread remaining mayo over top.
Sprinkle sugar, cheese and bacon over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Add water chestnuts.
Toss before serving.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Put egg in a cup and add enough water to equal 1 full cup. Blend lard and flour until crumbly. Add remaining ingredients. Blend until it forms a ball. Break into 6 or 7 smaller balls. Roll each into pie crust shape. This freezes very well.

title: party tarts
directions: Mix and form into 24 balls.
Using thumb, press into small tart pans.
Fill with the following:

title: beef pie
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients except egg and cheese.
Place flat crescent rolls in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Pour in meat mixture.
Pour egg evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes and then top with cheese.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix cheese and mayonnaise.
Add onions and peppers.
Spread over tortillas.
Roll up, wrapping each roll in wax paper. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before slicing and serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator for days.

title: turkey and rice dressing
directions: Remove neck and giblets; place in 3 1/2 cups chicken broth and simmer for 30 minutes.
Reserve broth.
In a 5 to 8 quart Dutch oven, melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute onions, celery and peppers.
Add parsley, chestnuts, apples, currants, pine nuts, cinnamon, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and Mahatma rice; mix thoroughly.
In microwave heat 2 packages of French's brown gravy mix with 2 cups turkey broth for 1 minute; stir.
Heat another minute.
Add to stuffing mixture and mix well.
Wash turkey and rub inside and out with margarine.
Season with salt and pepper. Fill chest cavity with stuffing.
Plac turkey in large pan.
Bake at 325° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: seasoned taco meat
directions: In a dutch oven, cook the beef and onions over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in the next 15 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve in taco shells with shredded cheese and salsa.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cook and cool potatoes.
Slice about 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick; layer sliced potatoes in a rectangular dish.
Cover with layer of dressing (sour cream, mayonnaise, horseradish, celery seed and salt).
Sprinkle with onion and parsley, which have been mixed together.
Continue layering in preceding manner until all ingredients are used.
Should be made 8 to 10 hours before serving.
Preferably overnight refrigeration.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jill's southern cookies
directions: Melt sugar and butter together and let cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread thin in a shallow pan.
Bake at 325° until done, about 25 minutes.

title: lo-cal vegetable soup
directions: Simmer all together about 1 hour.

title: ghost chocolate cups(mom or dad will help with hard parts.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding and milk together.

Beat with a whisk about 1 minute. Gently stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies. Evenly divide in individual custard cups (5 or 6) or juice glasses (5 or 6), a tablespoon of the crushed cookie, the pudding mixture, another layer of cookies. Place a dollop of Cool Whip by spoonful on the cookie crumbs to create a ghost head.
With three cookie crumbs, make two eyes and a nose on the dollop of Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in large skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and 1 1/2 cups water, mixing well.
Simmer, covered, for 25 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally, adding more water if necessary.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix pudding cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan, then mix 1 egg, cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice until smooth.
Pour this mixture over baked cake and sprinkle with other half of cake mix. Bake 15 minutes more.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fresh peach salad
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and mayonnaise; pour over peaches.
Mix well and chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls into a lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Firmly press perforations to seal. Combine eggs, bacon, cheese and mushrooms. Pour over prepared crust. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: wild leek soup
directions: Combine broth, leeks, salt and pepper in large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until leeks are tender.
Add chicken and rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: *Tuna or chicken can also be used.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scrub and dry potatoes.
Prick with fork in several places.
Place on baking sheet and bake 45 to 60 minutes.
When above is completed, slice about 1 inch from top of each potato, remove skin from slice and discard.
Remove pulp from each potato into a bowl, add potato pulp from slice.
Mash pulp. Add sour cream, herbs, and parmesan cheese.
Mash until smooth, if necessary add a small amount of milk, 1 Tbsp. at a time until desired consistency.
Stuff mixture into potato shells and place in a shallow pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: golden twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut lengthwise slice from top of each potato; scoop out potato, leaving 1/8-inch shell.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Add whole jar of Zesty Italian dressing mix.
Cover and let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Add Salad Supreme seasoning, tomato and cucumber. Ready to serve.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Split Twinkies; place in large casserole dish.
Mix pudding according to directions in separate bowl.
Pour 1/2 of pudding over Twinkies.
Spread 1/2 of strawberries and 1/2 of bananas. Spread other half of pudding over strawberries and bananas.
Pour remaining strawberries and bananas.
Then top with Cool Whip.

title: jean's taco salad
directions: Beat together cream cheese with milk.
Smear on bottom of a good size platter.
Cover with taco sauce.
Chop tomatoes very fine; squeeze excess juice from tomatoes.
Spread tomatoes on top of salsa.
Spread all of taco cheese, then sprinkle the Velveeta Mexican shredded cheese.
Mix evenly.
Shred lettuce on top 1/4 inch thick.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Mix all together, except corn flakes.
Add corn flakes to top. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: neiman-marcus squares
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Stir together until moistened.
Pat mixture into bottom of well-greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Beat remaining 2 eggs lightly, then beat in cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour over mixture in pan spreading evenly.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.
Cool pan on wire rack to room temperature. Makes 4 dozen bars.

title: don's world famous pepper ball
directions: Mix ingredients well and add pepper in the mix.
Allow to harden in the refrigerator.
Roll into a ball.
Generously cover with the pepper.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water and crab boil.
Potatoes are done when pierced easily with a fork (approximately 25 minutes).
Drain and rinse with cold water; let cool for 20 minutes.
Quarter each potato, leaving skins on.
Add all other ingredients, except bacon bits.
Mix thoroughly, then top with bacon bits.
Serve immediately.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender.
Combine cooled carrots, onion and pepper.
In another container, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: ice cream fudge
directions: In large microwave bowl, melt chips and bark in microwave until liquified, stirring occasionally.
Then quickly stir in softened ice cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spring lime jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O; let cool for 20 minutes.
Add crushed pineapple and orange slices, drained.
Fold in Cool Whip or mound on top, if preferred.

title: stuffed kaiser rolls
directions: Add cooked broccoli to cooked beef and onion.
Cut 1 pound Velveeta over meat mixture and let it melt.
Remove from heat. Cut off tops of buns; pull out inside of bottom buns.
Fill with beef mixture; put tops on.
Roll buns in melted seasoned margarine.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake on cookie sheet in 375° to 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.
Serves 6.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in large pan.
Take off heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add cereal and stir to mix thoroughly.
Empty box of powdered sugar into large paper bag.
Add coated Crispix cereal to paper bag.
Close and shake until well covered.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake as directed on package.
Cool and cut into 2-inch cubes.
Mash strawberries and sweeten to taste.
Reserve a few fresh ones for garnish.
Mix pudding as directed on package. If too thick, add more milk.
In a punch bowl, layer cake, pudding, strawberries, pineapple and Cool Whip until all gone, ending with Cool Whip.
Garnish with strawberry slices.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool and peel.
Cut potatoes into small pieces; mix potatoes, cheese, pimiento, onion, pepper and bread well.
Add butter, then milk, just so you can see.
Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes and bake at 300° to 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 11 to 12.

title: 3 layer bar cookies
directions: In 8-inch square dish, microwave (High) butter 30 seconds. Stir in crumbs and sugar; combine.
Pat evenly in dish.
Microwave (High) 2 minutes.
Cool.
In small mixing bowl, combine nuts, coconut and condensed milk.
Layer mixture evenly over crust. Microwave (High) 3 to 4 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Sprinkle chips evenly on top .
Microwave (High) 1 to 2 minutes and spread melted chocolate to frost.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and cook slowly over low heat until thickened (approximately 4 minutes).
After thick, stir in shelled pecans.
Pour over pecans on waxed paper or a buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and separate.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in corn meal. Combine egg and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Break salmon into bite size pieces and fold into batter.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown, about 4 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, water, syrup and peanuts in black iron skillet. Cook until thick and nuts pop and mixture turns a golden brown. Add soda as you remove from heat and stir vigorously.
Pour into greased sheet pan, stirring and pouring very thin.
When cool, crack into pieces.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, including liquor from mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Do not dilute soup.
Tuna can be used in place of chicken.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in refrigerator.

title: snack club crackers
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and pecans. Spread over crackers. Bake on cookie sheet approximately 10 minutes at 350°.

title: daiquiri pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin and sugar in saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup of water and the eggs. Blend well. Add remaining water. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat. Stir in rum. Chill.
Thoroughly blend Cool Whip into chilled mixture. Spoon into pie crust and chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and lime slices, if desired.

title: pear relish
directions: Run pears, onions and peppers through meat chopper.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes after it begins to boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Use large plate.
Place cream cheese in center.
Cover with drained crab.
Cover with sauce.
Place crackers around sides. Use knife to cut through 3 layers.
Serves 10.
Enjoy!

title: choconut caramel bars
directions: In double boiler, melt shortening and chocolate chips over hot, not boiling, water. Stir until smooth. Remove from heat and pour half into an 8-inch foil lined pan.
Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes). Return rest to low heat.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Make brownies. While hot, poke holes and pour liqueur over. Let cool. Make mousse. Crush candy bars. Cut brownies into bite-size pieces. Layer brownies, mousse, Cool Whip and crushed candy. Repeat (2 layers). Use a deep bowl.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix half the flour with 7-Up and sour cream.
Then add rest of flour gradually, working it in.
Roll to desired thickness and cut into biscuit shape.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut-pineapple cream pie(an original recipe)
directions: In a large bowl, mix milk and lemon juice with a spoon until well blended. Add Cool Whip and mix, then add rest of ingredients and mix well. Pour into pie crusts. Invert plastic lid on top of pies. Chill several hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour sauce for chicken
directions: Melt butter and mix all other ingredients.
Make as much as is needed for chicken to be covered and a little extra as a sauce. Cook chicken under broiler or on a grill with a container to collect extra sauce for gravy.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: After chopping all of the ingredients, put in large pan.
Add 1 cup water.
Steam until done.
Add salt to taste.

title: mom's pecan puffs
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and blend until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour and pecans.
Stir into butter mixture.
Roll into small balls.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a slow oven, 300°, for about 45 minutes.
While hot, roll the puffs in confectioners sugar.
When cool, roll again.
(I use a paper bag and carefully shake them in the sugar.) Makes 32 (1 1/2-inch) balls.

title: jackpot casserole
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven; drain.
Add all ingredients, except cheese.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Add cheese.
Let melt.

title: easy stew
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, drain, and set aside.
Saute onion in drippings.
Boil potatoes in enough water to cover, when boiling, add salt to water.
Add beef
and onion when potatoes are tender.
Cook 10-15 minutes on medium heat.

title: sesame seed cookies(china)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix in egg and vanilla well.
Sift flour, soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.
Form dough into small balls; roll in sesame seed.
Place on greased baking sheets; flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 370°.
Small drop of red food coloring may be placed in center of each cookie before baking if desired.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: chicken vegetable bisque
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender; add remaining ingredients. Heat, stirring occasionally.
(May need more milk, lemon juice, hot sauce (go easy) and salt.)
Makes 7 cups.
I make mine in crock-pot.

title: sour cream banana loaf
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well, then add eggs and bananas; mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream and add to banana mixture.
Last blend in nuts.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tested for doneness.
Cool 20 minutes, then remove from pan.
Cool.
It can be stored in refrigerator for several weeks, or in the freezer for 2 months.
Let it stand 24 hours before cutting.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute pimento, pepper, onion and mushroom only until crisp. Blend soup, half and half and Velveeta cheese and blend with sauteed vegetables.
Mix all together and put in 9 x 13 pan (or larger).
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: easy mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese, onion, salt and milk.
Add potatoes.
Mix.
Put in greased baking dish.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: chuk's loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Shape into a loaf pan.
Glaze top with catsup and bake at 350°
for about 60 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with any chips.

title: vidalia onion classic casserole
directions: Saute Vidalias in butter until they are transparent.
Add flour, then chicken broth and sherry.
When slightly thickened, transfer to a medium casseorle dish.
Top with bread crumbs and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vanilla.
Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet. (Optional:
Roll in ground nuts.)

title: red beans and sausage
directions: Cook red beans in a large saucepan until done and soupy. Rinse hot sausage and cut up into small pieces.
Put into beans. Add salt, sugar and pepper.
Let simmer for about 1/2 hour over low flame.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Let ice cream set out in a large bowl until just begins to soften.
Break up cookies in small pieces.
Mix with ice cream with large spoon or mixer.
Add Cool Whip; mix.
Put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex or metal pan.
Refreeze in freezer.

title: old-fashioned vanilla cake
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla together until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Beat 1/2 minute. Turn into 3 well-greased, lightly floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 25 minutes or until done. Cool on rack.
Spread with frosting when cold.
Yields 12 servings.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Melt butter and flour.
Make a smooth paste and stir constantly over medium heat until a rich brown.
Be careful not to burn.
Add water, tomatoes and okra (chopped fine).
Cook slowly for 1 hour. Add crab meat, oysters, shrimp (cleaned) and fish (boned and skinned).
Cook 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Soup should be thick.
Add steamed rice to each serving.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk and slightly beaten egg yolks.
After thickened, add vanilla and oleo.

title: fresh peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together in order listed.
Pour into lightly greased and floured Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes and then place on cooling rack.
Cool.

title: vanilla eclairs
directions: Prepare Basic Eclair dough.
Put through a pastry tube or spread with a spoon, making strips 4 x 1 1/2-inches on greased baking sheet.
Bake and cool as directed in Basic Eclair recipe.

title: sweet potato caramel
directions: Mix together brown sugar and flour.
Melt oleo in frypan, then add brown sugar and flour mixture.
Stir in milk and salt.
Cook caramel until soft ball.
Place potatoes in flat pan and sprinkle lightly with flour.
Pour cooked caramel over potatoes.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: You will need one package of cupcake papers.

title: crisfield crab skimmers
directions: Mix crab meat, green pepper, celery, onions, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, lemon pepper seasoning and Old Bay seasoning.
Put muffins on cookie sheet.
Place under broiler and toast slightly.
Remove.
Mound crab mixture on muffins.
Top with cheese of choice.
Broil 4 inches from heat until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serve at once.

title: ham salad
directions: Flake ham and add juice that is in can.
Add eggs, pickles and mayonnaise.
Mix well.

title: clear vegetable soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over high heat, heat broth, water, carrot and celery to boiling.
Add macaroni.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer until macaroni is done, about 20 minutes.
When serving, sprinkle with parsley in each bowl.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Empty 1 package spaghetti sauce mix into saucepan.
Blend in one can tomato paste and 3 cans water.
Add the olive oil or salad oil.
Bring to boil; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Crumble and brown the ground beef; add to sauce.
Makes enough sauce for 12 ounces spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: twisted macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain well.
Make sure macaroni is cool before adding dressing or it will curdle.
Blend all ingredients well and mix with macaroni.
Best made 24 hours before serving.
Mix before serving.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to package directions for 7 minutes; drain.
Arrange cooked macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper in buttered 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole.
Pour melted butter or margarine over macaroni.
Carefully pour milk into casserole at one corner.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marinated steak a la burt
directions: Let the steak marinate in this for at least 30 minutes; 1 hour is even better.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all together, pour in pie crust and put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine butter and onion in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook at High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add broth, milk, salt and pepper; stir until smooth.
Cook at medium heat for 8 to 9 minutes or until soup is slightly thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Add broccoli and puree in batches in food processor or blender.
Put broccoli into casserole dish.
Cook on Medium for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs.
Add jam. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk.
Dredge raisins and nuts in 1/4 cup flour and add to batter.
Pour into a well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Place small tin of water on rack beside cake while baking to keep top from getting hard.
